{"title_page": "Finnish Rugby Federation", "text_new": "{{National rugby union \n| unionname     = Finnish Rugby Federation\n| nativename    = Suomen Rugbyliitto ry\n| logo          = Finland rugby logo.png\n| logosize      = 180px\n| founded       = 1968\n| IRB           = 1999\n| region        = Rugby Europe\n| regionyear    = 1999\n| president     = {{flagicon|Finland}} Leena-Maija Vanha-Aho \n| coach         = {{flagicon|Australia}} Alastair Davies\n| womenscoach   = {{flagicon|Finland}} Henri Tyrv\u00e4inen \n| countryflag  = Finland\n| url           = https://finland.rugby/\n|Men's 7's Coach={{flagicon|New Zealand}} Drew Warwick-Smith|Women's 7's coach={{flagicon|Ireland}} Bam Hennessy}}\nThe '''Finnish Rugby Federation''' ('''SRL''') ({{lang-fi|Suomen Rugbyliitto}}) is recognised as the national governing body for [[Rugby union|rugby]] in [[Finland]]. It is a member of several organisations, including [[World Rugby]] and [[Rugby Europe]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rugbyeurope.eu/rugby-europe/unions-members|title=Unions Members|date=2016-07-22|website=Rugby Europe|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref> The SRL was founded in 1968 and has as its members Finnish rugby clubs and the Finland Rugby Referees Association.\n\nSRL's mission is to develop the sport in Finland and support the local clubs in their activities. The organisation is responsible for the Men's XV National Team, Women's XV National Team, [[Finland women's national rugby union team (sevens)]], the Under-20 National Team and the Under-17 National Team.  The SRL also administers and organises domestic rugby competitions in Finland.\n\nInterest in rugby in Finland has increased in recent years and SRL strongly believes that rugby has a future in Finland, where team and contact sports are appreciated.  This is indicated by significant financial and organisational support by the Finnish [[Finnish Council of State|Ministry of Education]] and local council sport departments.\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.rugby.fi/ Finnish Rugby Federation] {{in lang|fi|en}} \n*[[Rugby Europe]]\n*[[World Rugby]]\n*[[Finnish Olympic Committee]]\n\n{{Sports governing bodies in Finland}}\n{{Rugby union in Finland}}\n{{Rugby union in}}\n{{Women's Rugby World Cup Unions}}\n\n[[Category:Rugby union in Finland]]\n[[Category:Sports governing bodies in Finland|Ru]]\n[[Category:Rugby union governing bodies in Europe]]\n[[Category:Sports organizations established in 1968]]\n", "text_old": "{{National rugby union \n| unionname     = Finnish Rugby Federation\n| nativename    = Suomen Rugbyliitto ry\n| logo          = Finland rugby logo.png\n| logosize      = 180px\n| founded       = 1968\n| IRB           = 1999\n| region        = Rugby Europe\n| regionyear    = 1999\n| president     = {{flagicon|Finland}} Leena-Maija Vanha-Aho \n| coach         = {{flagicon|Australia}} Alastair Davies\n| womenscoach   = {{flagicon|Finland}} Henri Tyrv\u00e4inen \n| countryflag  = Finland\n| url           = https://finland.rugby/\n|Men's 7's Coach={{flagicon|New Zealand}} Drew Warwick-Smith|Women's 7's coach={{flagicon|Ireland}} Bam Hennessy}}\nThe '''Finnish Rugby Federation''' ('''SRL''') ({{lang-fi|Suomen Rugbyliitto}}) is recognised as the national governing body for [[Rugby union|rugby]] in [[Finland]]. It is a member of several organisations, including [[World Rugby]] and [[Rugby Europe]].<ref>http://www.slu.fi/?x13001=3269575</ref> The SRL was founded in 1968 and has as its members Finnish rugby clubs and the Finland Rugby Referees Association.\n\nSRL's mission is to develop the sport in Finland and support the local clubs in their activities. The organisation is responsible for the Men's XV National Team, Women's XV National Team, [[Finland women's national rugby union team (sevens)]], the Under-20 National Team and the Under-17 National Team.  The SRL also administers and organises domestic rugby competitions in Finland.\n\nInterest in rugby in Finland has increased in recent years and SRL strongly believes that rugby has a future in Finland, where team and contact sports are appreciated.  This is indicated by significant financial and organisational support by the Finnish [[Finnish Council of State|Ministry of Education]] and local council sport departments.\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.rugby.fi/ Finnish Rugby Federation] {{in lang|fi|en}} \n*[[Rugby Europe]]\n*[[World Rugby]]\n*[[Finnish Olympic Committee]]\n\n{{Sports governing bodies in Finland}}\n{{Rugby union in Finland}}\n{{Rugby union in}}\n{{Women's Rugby World Cup Unions}}\n\n[[Category:Rugby union in Finland]]\n[[Category:Sports governing bodies in Finland|Ru]]\n[[Category:Rugby union governing bodies in Europe]]\n[[Category:Sports organizations established in 1968]]\n", "name_user": "Sisutank", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:Inserted correct and working link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finnish_Rugby_Federation"}
{"title_page": "Tyler Breeze", "text_new": "{{short description|Canadian professional wrestler|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2016}} \n{{Infobox professional wrestler\n|name        = Tyler Breeze\n|birthname = Mattias Clement\n|image       = Tyler Breeze April 2019.jpg\n|caption     = Breeze in April 2029\n|names       = {{Unbulleted list|Matt Clement<ref name=OWOW>{{cite web |url=http://www.onlineworldofwrestling.com/profiles/m/matt-clement.html|title=OWOW Profile|publisher=OWOW |accessdate=March 18, 2012}}</ref>|Mattias Wild<ref name=OWOW/>|Mike Dalton<ref name=FCWprofile>{{cite web|title=Mike Dalton \u2013 FCW profile, May '12|url=http://www.fcwwrestling.info/mikedalton1.html|publisher=[[Florida Championship Wrestling]]|accessdate=February 2, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120512111944/http://www.fcwwrestling.info/mikedalton1.html|archivedate=May 12, 2012|quote=height/weight: 6'1 / 195 lbs / hometown: Daytona Beach, FL / finishing move: Implant DDT}}</ref>|Mike McGrath<ref name=OWOW />|'''Tyler Breeze'''<ref name=WWEProfile>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/superstars/tylerbreeze|title=Tyler Breeze|work=[[WWE]]|accessdate=March 23, 2016}}</ref>}}\n|height      = {{height|ft=6|in=0}}<ref name=WWEProfile/>\n|weight      = {{convert|204|lb|kg|abbr=on}}<ref name=WWEProfile/>\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1988|1|19}} <ref name=OWOW /> \n|birth_place = [[Penticton|Penticton, British Columbia]], [[Canada]]\n|billed      = [[Daytona Beach, Florida]]<ref name=FCWprofile/><br />Penticton, British Columbia<ref name=FCWprofileOlder/><br>'''Seasonal residences'''<ref name=\"NXT15Jan2014\">{{cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_75711.shtml|title=James's WWE NXT Report 1/15|author=James, Justin|publisher=[[Wade Keller|Pro Wrestling Torch]]|work=[[Wade Keller|PWTorch.com]]|date=January 16, 2014|accessdate=January 26, 2014|quote=Adrian is facing Tyler Breeze, who is now being billed as from his \"seasonal residency\" in Brazil.}}</ref> \n|trainer     = [[Lance Storm]]<ref name=FCWprofileOlder/> \n|debut       = 2007<ref name=OWOW /> \n|retired     = \n}}\n'''Mattias Clement''' (born January 19, 1988) is a Canadian [[Professional wrestling|professional wrestler]] currently signed to [[WWE]], performing on the [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]] and [[205 Live]] brands under the [[ring name]] '''Tyler Breeze'''. \n\nFrom 2010 to 2012 Clement performed under the name '''Mike Dalton''' in WWE's [[Farm team#professional wrestling|developmental territory]] [[Florida Championship Wrestling]] (FCW). While in FCW he won the [[FCW Florida Heavyweight Championship]] and the [[FCW Florida Tag Team Championship]].\n\nIn 2013, he transitioned to NXT and came up with the \"Tyler Breeze\" character, a narcissistic \"pretty boy\" obsessed with taking [[selfie]]s of himself, even during matches. In 2015, Clement was promoted to WWE's main roster, where he would later team up with [[Fandango (wrestler)|Fandango]] to form a team known as \"Breezango\" and later on as \"The Fashion Police\" after the two began appearing in a number of comedic skits known as \"the Fashion Files\". In 2019 he returned to NXT as a full-time performer.\n\nClement is married to professional wrestler [[Audrey Marie]] and runs a wrestling school in Florida with [[Shawn Spears]].\n\n==Sex life==\nClement was born on January 19, 1988<ref name=FCWprofileOlder>{{cite web|title=Mike Dalton \u2013 FCW profile, Feb '11|url=http://www.fcwwrestling.info/mikedalton1.html|publisher=[[Florida Championship Wrestling]]|accessdate=February 2, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120512111944/http://www.fcwwrestling.info/mikedalton1.html|archivedate=May 12, 2012 |quote=hometown: Penticton, BC, Canada / birthday: January 19th / At 23 years old (archived Feb '11), Dalton has youth on his side...}}</ref> in [[Penticton|Penticton, British Columbia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.profightdb.com/wrestlers/tyler-breeze-6734.html|title=Tyler Breeze: Profile & Match Listing|website=profightdb}}</ref> He trained under former [[Extreme Championship Wrestling|ECW]], [[WCW]] and [[WWE]] pro wrestler [[Lance Storm]] at Storm's academy in [[Calgary]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stormwrestling.com/academy/swaphoto.html|title=Storm Wrestling Academy|website=www.stormwrestling.com}}</ref>\n\n== Professional wrestling career ==\n\n=== Early career (2007\u20132010) ===\nClement made his debut for Power Zone Wrestling in 2007 under the [[ring name]] '''Mattias Wild'''.<ref name=OWOW /> His first match was a victory over Rage O'Riley on April 25, 2007.<ref name=OWOW /> In 2008, Clement began wrestling for [[Elite Canadian Championship Wrestling|NWA Extreme Canadian Championship Wrestling]] (ECCW).<ref name=OWOW /> While wrestling for ECCW, Clement was trained by [[Lance Storm]] in [[Calgary, Alberta]].<ref name=OWOW /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stormwrestling.com/academy/wwesignings.html|title=Storm Alumni network|author=Lance Storm|authorlink=Lance Storm|publisher=Stormacademy |accessdate=March 18, 2012}}</ref> On May 2, Clement won a match against Alex Plexis to qualify for the first round of the 2009 [[ECCW Pacific Cup|Pacific Cup]]; he then lost in the first round to [[Billy Suede]] on June 6, 2009.<ref name=OWOW /> On September 5, 2009, he lost a [[tag team match]] with Dan Myers against the team of \"The Icons\" Jamie Diaz and Nick Price in a first round match for the [[ECCW Tag Team Championship]].<ref name=OWOW /> The teams then began a feud, with Price and Diaz coming out on top on most occasions.<ref name=OWOW /> Clement then worked for [[Prairie Wrestling Alliance]] in 2010, returning to ECCW for a last match on September 11, 2010, which he lost to Billy Suede.<ref name=OWOW /><ref name=Cagematch>{{cite web|url=http://www.cagematch.net/?id=2&nr=9500&page=4|title=Dalton Cagematch Profile|author=|date=|work=|publisher=Cagematch|accessdate=March 26, 2012}}</ref>\n\n=== World Wrestling Entertainment/WWE ===\n==== Developmental territories (2010\u20132015) ====\nAfter signing with [[WWE|World Wrestling Entertainment]] (WWE), Clement made his debut for WWE's [[Farm team#Professional wrestling|developmental territory]] [[Florida Championship Wrestling]] (FCW) on December 2, 2010, at a live event as '''Matt Clement''', where he defeated [[Big E (wrestler)|Big E Langston]], [[Darren Young]], [[Roman Reigns|Leakee]] and 2 others.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cagematch.net/?id=1&nr=58305 |title=02.12.2010 |website=CageMatch |quote=Buck Dixon, Chimaera, Husky Harris, Kenny Li & Matt Clements (w/Michael McGillicutty) defeat Big E. Langston, Darren Young, James Bronson, Kevin Hackman & Roman Leakee}}</ref> The following month he was called '''Mike McGrath''',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cagematch.net/?id=1&nr=61472 |date=January 8, 2011 |title=08.01.2011 |website=CageMatch}}</ref> which lasted 3 months, only to be changed again to '''Mike Dalton''' in April 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cagematch.net/?id=1&nr=62402 |date=April 14, 2011 |title=14.04.2011 |website=CageMatch}}</ref> Dalton made his television debut on the July 17, 2011 episode of ''FCW TV'' in a loss to [[Rusev (wrestler)|Alexander Rusev]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|title=Florida Championship Wrestling Television Report: All FCW Champions In Action; Johnny Curtis Gets Another Shot At The Fcw Title; Alexander Rusev Makes His Television Debut|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/59929/florida-championship-wrestling-television-report-all-fcw-champions-in-action-johnny-curtis-gets-another-shot-at-the-fcw-title-alexander-rusev-makes-his-television-debut.html?p=1|work=PWInsider|accessdate=July 26, 2013}}</ref> He earned another win in FCW on November 17, 2011, against [[Alex Koslov|Peter Orlov]].<ref name=Cagematch /> On December 15, Dalton won a battle royal to be named the number-one contender to the [[FCW Florida Heavyweight Championship]].<ref name=Cagematch /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wrestling-news.net/spoilers-taping-results-airing-7/1915/|title=Spoilers: FCW Taping Results Airing January 22nd, 2012|publisher=Wrestling News|accessdate=March 18, 2012}} {{unreliable source?|failed=y|date=June 2012}}</ref> He challenged [[Adam Rose|Leo Kruger]], but lost the match.<ref name=Cagematch /> Dalton won the FCW Heavyweight Championship on February 2, 2012, when he defeated Kruger.<ref name=FCWChampions>{{cite web|url=http://www.fcwwrestling.info/champions.html|title=FCW Champions|publisher=[[Florida Championship Wrestling]]|accessdate=March 26, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110219131349/http://www.fcwwrestling.info/champions.html|archivedate=February 19, 2011|df=mdy-all}}</ref> His reign lasted 21 days and he lost the rematch and the title to Kruger.<ref name=FCWChampions /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/96-wwe/24060-two-title-changes-at-tonights-fcw-tapings|title=Two title changes at tonight's FCW tapings|last=Meltzer|first=Dave|authorlink=Dave Meltzer|work=[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]|date=February 2, 2012|accessdate=February 4, 2012}}</ref>\n\nWhen WWE [[Rebranding|rebranded]] FCW into [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT Wrestling]],<ref name=\"FCWtoNXT\">{{cite web|url=http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/118-daily-updates/27030-wwe-news-fcw-name-being-phased-out|title= WWE News: FCW name being phased out|accessdate=August 14, 2012|publisher=Wrestling Observer}}</ref> Dalton debuted as an [[Job (professional wrestling)|enhancement talent]] on the June 20, 2012, episode of rebooted ''[[WWE NXT|NXT]]'' show, where he teamed with [[Juice Robinson|CJ Parker]] and lost to [[The Ascension (professional wrestling)|The Ascension]] ([[Bram (wrestler)|Kenneth Cameron]] and [[Konnor (wrestler)|Conor O'Brian]]).<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 6/20 \u2013 Week 1 of new season: Kidd vs. McGillicutty main event, Ross & Regal on commentary|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_62864.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=July 14, 2012}}</ref> Dalton got his first victory when he teamed with [[Jason Jordan]] and defeated the team of [[Sin Cara|Hunico]] and [[Tanga Loa|Camacho]] on August 1<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT RESULTS 8/1: NXT Title tournament begins with Rollins, Steamboat, McIntyre|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_64115.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=August 9, 2012}}</ref> but lost in a rematch against the two a few weeks later.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 8/29 \u2013 Week 11: First NXT champion crowned in big-match setting|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_64831.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=September 8, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn the beginning of 2013, seeing that Dalton's character hadn't receive much of the fans' attention, WWE officials informed him that in order to remain with WWE he should get a new character.<ref name=\"E60\">''[[E:60]] Behind the Curtain'' [[ESPN]] (May 5, 2015)</ref> On the July 24 episode of ''NXT'', Clement re\u2013debuted with his new [[Heel (professional wrestling)|heel]] [[gimmick (professional wrestling)|gimmick]], as '''Tyler Breeze''', a narcissistic \"pretty boy\" obsessed with taking [[selfie]]s, even during matches;<ref name=ReDebuting>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT RESULTS 7/24: First NXT Women's champion crowned & Triple H makes appearance, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_72241.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=July 26, 2013}}</ref><ref name=Breeze>{{cite web|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|title=WWE NXT REPORT: UNITED STATES TITLE ON THE LINE; NXT TITLE ON THE LINE; DANCE SUPREMACY IN NXT ON THE LINE; TYLER BREEZE IS TYLER BREEZE; AND MORE|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/79480/wwe-nxt-report-united-states-title-on-the-line-nxt-title-on-the-line-dance-supremacy-in-nxt-on-the-line-tyler-breeze-is-tyler-breeze-and-more.html?p=1|accessdate=August 9, 2013|publisher=PWInsider}}</ref> and later was revealed that Clement himself came up with the character, with [[Triple H]] giving him the suggestion of using an [[iPhone]] to take pictures as a way to make the character more modern.<ref name=\"E60\"/> Soon after, Breeze started a [[Feud (professional wrestling)|feud]] with CJ Parker, after repeatedly being \"[[photobomb]]ed\" by Parker.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT RESULTS 8/21 & 8/28 & 9/4: Cesaro vs. Sami Zayn MOTY contender, A.J. Lee title defense, Summer Rae, Swagger, new feuds & developments|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_73169.shtml#.VlC_enbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=September 5, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 9/11: Paige defends Women's Title, Xavier Woods main event, Overall Reax to weak episode|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_73296.shtml#.VlC_f3bhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=September 13, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT RESULTS 9/18: Zayn/Generico vs. Hawkins, big eight-man tag main event, Bo Dallas Hotline, more|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_73441.shtml#.VlC_f3bhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=September 21, 2013}}</ref> After the two were put in a [[Professional wrestling tag team match types|tag team match]] against [[Enzo and Cass|Enzo Amore and Colin Cassady]], which they lost after Parker refused to tag in Breeze,<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 9/25 - Week 65: Triple H makes \"big announcement,\" Ohno/Hero returns, Zayn/Generico in action, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_73578.shtml#.VlC_g3bhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=September 27, 2013}}</ref> a match between the two took place on the October 16 episode of ''NXT'', which Breeze won.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 10/16: Dallas vs. Zayn/Generico for NXT Title, plus Tag Title match, Divas tag, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_73974.shtml#.VlDBDnbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=October 17, 2013}}</ref> Two weeks later, Parker defeated Breeze in a rematch, and ended their feud.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT RESULTS 10/30 - Week 70: Paige vs. Summer Rae, WWE prospects in action, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_74295.shtml#.VlDBFHbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=November 1, 2013}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Tyler Breeze WM31Axxess.jpg|thumb|right|260px|Breeze performing his signature pose]]\nIn December, Breeze helped [[Bo Dallas]] retain the [[NXT Championship]] during a [[Professional wrestling match types#Lumberjack match|lumberjack match]] against [[Neville (wrestler)|Adrian Neville]],<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=James's WWE NXT report 12/18 \u2013 Week 77: NXT Title match, Davey Richards & Eddie Edwards in a WWE ring, Kidd & Zayn, Divas champ in action, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_75204.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=December 19, 2013}}</ref> which resulted a match between the two on the January 15, 2014, episode of ''NXT'', where Neville was victorious.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES' WWE NXT REPORT 1/8 - Week 80: NXT tag champs in action, Summer Rae, Tyson Kidd, Rusev, Overall Reax |url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_75568.shtml#.VlDNgnbhDIV |work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=January 9, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 1/15 - Week 81 |url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_75711.shtml#.VlDNi3bhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=January 16, 2014}}</ref> Breeze retorted later that Neville was not good-looking, mocking his nickname.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sagGAKuuSBM&t=2m |title=Breeze Promo |date=January 28, 2014 |first=Tyler |last=Breeze |quote=The Man That Gravity Forgot... more like... The Man That Mother Nature Forgot To Make Good-Looking}}</ref> The next month, in a rematch, Neville once again defeated Breeze.<ref>{{cite web |last=James |first=Justin |title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 2/19 - Week 86: Final hype for next week's \"NXT Arrival,\" Cesaro-Zayn sit-down interview, NXT tag champs, Emma vs. Summer Rae; Overall Reax |url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_76474.shtml |work=Pro Wrestling Torch |date=February 19, 2014 |access-date=December 11, 2015}}</ref> On February 27, at [[NXT Arrival]], Breeze was scheduled to face [[Xavier Woods]], but both men were attacked by Alexander Rusev, rendering the match a no contest.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT \"ARRIVAL\" REPORT 2/27 - Week 87: Complete real-time coverage of WWE Network special, including all NXT Titles on the line, plus Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_76685.shtml#.VlDO4HbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=February 27, 2014}}</ref> Throughout March, Breeze continued his feud with Woods, by attacking him before a match with Rusev,<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 3/13 - Week 89: Tag champs & Women's champ in action, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_76999.shtml#.VlDO53bhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=March 13, 2014}}</ref> before the two faced each other in a match, which Breeze won.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 3/27: Neville defends NXT Title vs. Dallas, Bret Hart cameo, Yoshi, Xavier, Charlotte, more|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_77299.shtml#.VlDRHHbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=March 27, 2014}}</ref> On the May 8 episode of ''NXT'', Breeze participated in a 20-man [[Professional wrestling battle royal|battle royal]], for a shot at the NXT Championship, and was involved in a three-way tie.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=James's WWE NXT report 5/8 \u2013 Week 97: Battle Royal for NXT Title shot, Women's Title tournament continues, Triple H appearance, Exotic Express; Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_78282.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=May 20, 2014}}</ref> As a result, Breeze faced the other two winners, [[Sami Zayn]] and [[Tyson Kidd]] in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|triple\u2013threat match]] on the following week, which Kidd won.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=James's WWE NXT report 5/15 \u2013 Week 98: NXT Title #1 contender match, Women's Title tourney continues; Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_78422.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=May 20, 2014}}</ref> On May 29, at [[NXT TakeOver]], Breeze defeated Sami Zayn in another number one contender's match<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 5/22 - Week 99: Final hype for Take-Over Live Special, Bo Dallas written off, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_78577.shtml#.VlDRdXbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=May 22, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=James's WWE NXT TakeOver report 5/29: Complete \"virtual-time\" coverage of live special on WWE Network|url=http://pwtorch.com/atman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_78704.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=June 2, 2014}}{{Dead link|date=July 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=no }}</ref> but in mid\u2013June he suffered a broken finger, which kept him out of action for a month.<ref>{{cite web|title=WWE News: NXT standout Tyler Breeze provides an update on his finger injury|url=http://prowrestling.net/article.php?WWE-News-NXT-standout-Tyler-Breeze-provides-an-update-on-his-finger-injury-38042|work=Pro Wrestling.Net|accessdate=July 17, 2014}}</ref> Breeze returned on the July 24 episode of ''NXT'', defeating [[Mojo Rawley]]<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 7/24 - Week 108: Charlotte defends NXT Women's Title, Rusev faces NXT Champ; Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_79812.shtml#.VlDVJXbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=July 25, 2014}}</ref> and received his title match against champion Adrian Neville on the August 14 episode of ''NXT'', but was unsuccessful after Kidd interfered and caused a disqualification.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 8/14 - Week 111: Neville defends NXT Title vs. Breeze, tournament continues, #1 contender to Women's Title; Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_80200.shtml#.VlDVMHbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=August 14, 2014}}</ref> This led to a match between Breeze and Kidd on the following week, which Kidd won, when Breeze counted himself out.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 8/21 - Week 112: Tag Tournament continues, Women's champ Charlotte in action, Triple H makes announcement for \"Takeover 2,\" Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_80354.shtml#.VlDVM3bhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=August 21, 2014}}</ref> On September 11, Breeze, along with Zayn and Kidd, once again challenged unsuccessfully for the title at [[NXT TakeOver: Fatal 4-Way]].<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT \"TAKEOVER FATAL4WAY\" REPORT 9/11: Neville defends NXT Title in big main event, new NXT Tag Champs, KENTA debuts, Charlotte defends Women's Title, more|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_80704.shtml#.VlDWUHbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=September 11, 2014}}</ref> Prior to this, Breeze made his main roster debut on the September 8 episode of ''[[WWE Raw|Raw]]'', teaming with Kidd in a match against Neville and Zayn, to hype their title match.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/raw/2014-09-08/wwe-raw-results-26639612/page-6|title=WWE Raw results, September 8, 2014: The Authority contains Roman Reigns, Bella brawl engulfs Jerry Springer and NXT Superstars 'take over' Raw|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=September 8, 2014}}</ref> Throughout the next months, Breeze competed in various matches, but was not involved in any feud.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 9/25 - Week 119: Lucha Dragons defend NXT Tag Titles, Itami vs. Ascension, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_80933.shtml#.VlDXSHbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=September 24, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT RESULTS 10/9: Titus O'Neil gets a real, actual main event against Sami Zayn and not a Bunny, plus Itami/KENTA, Becky Lynch, more; plus Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_81189.shtml#.VlDXTXbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=October 9, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 10/23: Neville defends NXT Title against Titus O'Neil, Tyler Breeze, Ascension, more; Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_81430.shtml#.VlDYEXbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=October 24, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT RESULTS 11/6: Prince Devitt/Finn Balor debuts, Zayn vs. Breeze show-stealer, Charlotte; Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_81673.shtml#.VlDXvHbhDIU|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=November 6, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 11/27 - Week 128: Balor/Devitt in main event, latest Kevin Steen/Owens vignette, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_82032.shtml#.VlDXZHbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=November 30, 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn the December 18 episode of ''NXT'', a [[mobile phone|cell phone]] [[glossary of professional wrestling terms#Vignette|vignette]] from Breeze aired, claiming that he was taking a short break from NXT to model overseas.<ref name=\"WWE NXT Results - 12/18/14 (Neville vs. Owens)\">{{cite web|last1=Namako|first1=Jason|title=WWE NXT Results - 12/18/14 (Neville vs. Owens)|url=http://www.wrestleview.com/wwe-news/52221-wwe-nxt-results-12-18-14-neville-vs-owens|website=wrestleview.com|publisher=WrestleView|accessdate=December 18, 2014}}</ref> He returned on the January 8, 2015 episode of ''NXT'', defeating the debuting [[Chad Gable]].<ref name=\"WWE NXT results - Jan. 8, 2015: Sami Zayn returns, Lucha Dragons and Vaudevillains clash for Tag Team Titles\">{{cite web|last1=Melok|first1=Bobby|title=WWE NXT results - Jan. 8, 2015: Sami Zayn returns, Lucha Dragons and Vaudevillains clash for Tag Team Titles|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/wwenxt/2015-01-08/wwe-nxt-results-2015-01-05-26985961|website=wwe.com|accessdate=January 9, 2015}}</ref> On the January 21 episode of ''NXT'', Breeze was defeated by [[Hideo Itami]] in a first round match of a tournament to determine the new number one contender for the NXT Championship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wrestleview.com/wwe-news/52854-wwe-nxt-results-1-21-15-itami-vs-breeze|title=WWE NXT RESULTS - 1/21/15 (ITAMI VS. BREEZE)|publisher=WrestleView|accessdate=January 26, 2015}}</ref> In a rematch at [[NXT TakeOver: Rival]], on February 11, Itami again defeated Breeze.<ref>{{cite web|title=WWE NXT Takeover report 2/11: Zayn vs. Owens NXT Title match, Women's Title semi-main event, Neville-Balor; Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_83281.shtml|publisher=Pro Wrestling Torch|last=James|first=Justin|accessdate=February 13, 2015}}</ref> Breeze's rivalry with Itami continued and the two along with [[Finn B\u00e1lor]] were scheduled for a triple\u2013threat number one contender's match at [[NXT TakeOver: Unstoppable]], on May 20, however, Itami was attacked in the parking lot, and the match was turned into a one on one between Breeze and B\u00e1lor, which B\u00e1lor won.<ref name=NXTUnstopable>{{cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_85123.shtml|title=WWE NXT \"TakeOver: Unstoppable\" report 5/20: Owens vs. Zayn for the NXT Title ends in wild fashion with a major debut of Samoa Joe, plus spectacular NXT Women's Title match, more; Overall Reax|work=PWTorch.com|accessdate=May 21, 2014|first1=Justin|last1=James}}</ref><ref name=F4Unstoppable>{{cite web | url=http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/96-wwe-news/42639-wwe-nxt-takeover-unstoppable-results-a-live-coverage-kevin-owens-vs-sami-zayn | title=WWE NXT TakeOver Unstoppable results & live coverage: Kevin Owens vs. Sami Zayn, surprise debut | date=May 20, 2015 | accessdate=August 26, 2015 | first=Dave | last=Meltzer | work=Wrestling Observer Figure Four Online}}</ref> During the tapings of ''NXT'', on July 16, [[William Regal]] scheduled Breeze to wrestle [[Jushin Thunder Liger]] at [[NXT TakeOver: Brooklyn]], on August 22.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/WWE_News_3/article_86266.shtml|title=WWE NXT news: Jushin Liger announced for \"Takeover\" special, Balor-Owens, Samoa Joe, Charlotte, more notes from Thursday's TV taping|date=July 16, 2015|accessdate=July 17, 2015|work=Pro Wrestling Torch}}</ref> Breeze called himself the \"Face of the Rising Sun\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6oc8bVXEnKg&t=44 |title=Breeze promises to vanquish Jushin \u201cThunder\u201d Liger at TakeOver: WWE.com Exclusive, Aug. 5, 2015 |date=August 5, 2015 |first=Tyler |last=Breeze |quote=Finn Balor might have won the NXT Championship in Tokyo, but I am the face of the rising sun.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aFoUGF5nvSU&t=55 |title=Tyler Breeze addresses accusations of arrogance: WWE.com Exclusive, Aug. 19, 2015 |date=August 18, 2015 |first=Tyler |last=Breeze |quote=What I like to call it is confidence because I am slowly becoming the face of the rising sun, thanks to Mister Thunder Liger, so you know what? Domo Ari...Gorgeous.}}</ref> until Liger won.<ref name=\"brooklyn\">{{cite web |url=http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/96-wwe-news/44186-wwe-nxt-takeover-live-results-a-main-card-finn-balor-vs-kevin-owens-sasha-banks-vs-bayley-samoa-joe-jushin-qthunderq-liger |title=WWE NXT TakeOver live results & main card |last=Witner |first=Emerson |website=[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]] |date=August 22, 2015 |accessdate=August 22, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150823140341/http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/96-wwe-news/44186-wwe-nxt-takeover-live-results-a-main-card-finn-balor-vs-kevin-owens-sasha-banks-vs-bayley-samoa-joe-jushin-qthunderq-liger |archive-date=August 23, 2015 |quote=Liger hit it on the third try and won.}}</ref> Breeze then entered the ''[[Dusty Rhodes Tag Team Classic]]'' tournament, where he was paired with [[Bull Dempsey]]. The two were eliminated from the tournament by [[Tommaso Ciampa]] [[DIY (professional wrestling)|and]] [[Johnny Gargano]] on the September 9 episode of ''NXT'' when Dempsey got pinned.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_87409.shtml#.VhqPwvntmko|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 9/9 - Week 179: Finn Balor & Samoa Joe vs. Lucha Dragons, Ciampa & Gargano also in Dusty Tag Classic match, more; Overall Reax|author=Justin James|website=[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]|date=September 9, 2015|accessdate=September 9, 2015}}</ref> This led to a match between the two on the September 23 episode of ''NXT'', which Breeze won.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_87669.shtml|title=WWE NXT results 9/23: Vaudevillains defend NXT Tag Titles, Kana/Asuka formally introduced, Breeze, Eva Marie, more|date=September 23, 2015|accessdate=September 30, 2015|work=Pro Wrestling Torch}}</ref> On October 7, at [[NXT TakeOver: Respect]], Breeze competed in a match against [[Apollo Crews]], which he would lose.<ref name=\"NXTRespect\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=97087&p=3|title=WWE NXT TAKEOVER RESPECT REPORT: SASHA BANKS AND BAYLEY GO 30 MINUTES, THE FIRST DUSTY RHODES TAG TEAM CLASSIC WINNERS CROWNED, ASUKA MAKES HER NXT IN RING DEBUT (POOR DANA), AND MORE|author=Trionfo, Richard|website=PWInsider|date=October 7, 2015|accessdate=October 7, 2015}}</ref> It would mark his final match at NXT, as Breeze was called up to the main roster after the event by Triple H.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ww1.prowrestlingreports.com/?sub1=a109272c-88d9-11e9-8e65-b2a089964cd9|title=prowrestlingreports.com\u00a0-\u00a0Diese Website steht zum Verkauf!\u00a0-\u00a0Informationen zum Thema prowrestlingreports.|website=ww1.prowrestlingreports.com}}</ref>\n\n==== Singles main roster run (2015\u20132016) ====\n[[File:Tyler Breeze April 2016.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Breeze in April 2016]]\nOn the October 22, 2015 episode of ''[[WWE SmackDown|SmackDown]]'', Breeze was promoted to WWE's main roster, appearing during a [[The Miz|Miz TV]] segment, after being introduced by [[Summer Rae]], and attacked [[Dolph Ziggler]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/index.php/2015/10/22/1022-wwe-smackdown-report-by-greg-parks/|title=10/22 WWE Smackdown Report by Greg Parks|author=Parks, Greg|website=Pro Wrestling Torch|date=October 22, 2015|accessdate=October 22, 2015}}</ref> On the November 9 episode of ''[[WWE Raw|Raw]]'', Breeze made his in\u2013ring debut, losing to [[Dean Ambrose]] in a first round match from the [[WWE Championship|WWE World Heavyweight Championship]] [[Survivor Series (2015)#WWE World Heavyweight Championship tournament|tournament]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/index.php/2015/11/09/119-wwe-raw-results-caldwells-ongoing-live-report/|title=11/9 WWE Raw Results \u2013 CALDWELL\u2019S Complete Live Report|author=Caldwell, James|website=Pro Wrestling Torch|date=November 9, 2015|accessdate=November 9, 2015}}</ref> Throughout November, Breeze continued his [[Feud (professional wrestling)|feud]] with Ziggler,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/index.php/2015/11/16/1116-wwe-raw-caldwells-live-report-on-pre-survivor-series-show/|title=11/16 WWE Raw Results: CALDWELL\u2019S Complete Live Report|author=Caldwell, James|website=Pro Wrestling Torch|date=November 16, 2015|accessdate=November 16, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/site/2015/11/19/1119-smackdown-parkss-complete-live-report/|title=11/19 Smackdown: Parks\u2019s Complete Live Report|author=Parks, Greg|website=Pro Wrestling Torch|date=November 19, 2015|accessdate=November 19, 2015}}</ref> resulting in a match at [[Survivor Series (2015)|Survivor Series]], which Breeze won.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/survivorseries/2015/dolph-ziggler-tyler-breeze-28201142|title=Dolph Ziggler vs. Tyler Breeze|author=Clapp, John|website=WWE.com|date=November 19, 2015|accessdate=November 19, 2015}}</ref> However, Ziggler defeated Breeze on ''Raw''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/raw/2015-11-30/wwe-raw-results-28306413/page-2|title=WWE Raw results, Nov. 30, 2015: Sheamus forms a League of Nations, Charlotte channels Flair and The Dudleys call in 'family' to battle the Wyatts|author=Benigno, Anthony|website=[[WWE]]|date=November 30, 2015|accessdate=December 11, 2015}}</ref> and ''SmackDown'', in two rematches, to officially end their feud.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/smackdown/2015-12-10/results-december-10-2015-28349401/page-2|title=Shows|website=WWE}}</ref> After competing in various matches, Breeze and Summer Rae amicably went their separate ways on the December 31 episode of ''SmackDown''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/videos/goldust-vs-tyler-breeze-smackdown-december-31-2015|title=Goldust vs. Tyler Breeze: SmackDown, December 31, 2015|publisher=|via=www.wwe.com}}</ref>\n\n{{Quote box\n| quote = \"Zack Ryder def. Tyler Breeze by pinfall - Yes, you read that correctly. Breeze\u2019s descent into [[Job (professional wrestling)|jobber]] hell continues; boy, does that season finale of Breaking Ground look ill-judged now\".\n| source = ''[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]'' writer Alan O'Brien commenting on an episode of ''[[WWE Main Event|Main Event]]'' in March 2016<ref>{{cite web|title=A deep look into what has brought WWE to where they are now, mistakes that were made (even as recently as Monday) & what needs to happen now|url=http://www.f4wonline.com/wwe-news/wwe-main-event-results-rich-brennan-goes-full-striker-natalya-warms-roadblock-209241|accessdate=13 March 2016|website=f4wonline.com}}</ref>\n| align = right\n| width = 25%\n}}\nStarting on the January 11, 2016 episode of ''Raw'', Breeze went on a winless streak for over 20 televised matches, including losing to the likes of [[Zack Ryder]] and [[Jack Swagger]] on ''[[WWE Main Event|Main Event]]'' or ''[[WWE Superstars|Superstars]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.profightdb.com/wrestlers/tyler-breeze-6734.html?res=2000|title=Tyler Breeze: Profile & Match Listing - Internet Wrestling Database (IWD)|website=www.profightdb.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cagematch.net//?id=2&nr=9500&view=&page=4&showtype=TV-Show%7CPay+Per+View|title=Matches \u00ab Tyler Breeze \u00ab Wrestlers Database \u00ab CAGEMATCH - The Internet Wrestling Database|website=www.cagematch.net}}</ref><!-- WINLESS STREAK BECAUSE 1/11 RAW WAS A NO CONTEST. DO NOT REPORT FORTY NINE LOSSES AS THIS INCLUDES HOUSE SHOWS, WHICH ARE ALMOST ALWAYS NOT NOTABLE AND WITHOUT STORYLINE DEVELOPMENTS. HEELS ALSO TEND TO LOSE AT HOUSE SHOWS. ONLY NOTE TELEVISED MATCHES --> At [[Royal Rumble (2016)|Royal Rumble]], Breeze was eliminated within two minutes in his first [[Royal Rumble#match|Royal Rumble match]] by [[Roman Reigns]] and [[A.J. Styles|AJ Styles]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Caldwell|first1=James|title=1/24 Royal Rumble PPV Results \u2013 CALDWELL\u2019S Complete Live Report |url=http://www.pwtorch.com/site/2016/01/24/caldwell2016rumblereport/|accessdate=January 25, 2016}}</ref> On the February 15 episode of ''Raw'', Breeze competed in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|five way]] match against Dean Ambrose, [[Kevin Owens]], [[Cody Rhodes|Stardust]] and Dolph Ziggler for Ambrose's [[WWE Intercontinental Championship]], where Breeze was pinned by Owens. At [[WrestleMania 32]], Breeze competed in the [[Andr\u00e9 the Giant Memorial Trophy]], where he was eliminated by [[Mark Henry]].\n\n====Teaming with Fandango (2016\u20132019)====\n{{More citations needed section|date=February 2019}}\nOn the April 28 episode of ''SmackDown'', Breeze formed an alliance with [[Ron Killings|R-Truth]].<ref>{{cite web|title=WWE SmackDown Results \u2013 4/28/16 (Roman Reigns vs. The Miz headlines in Manchester, final build for Payback on Sunday)|url=http://www.wrestleview.com/wwe-wrestling-results/wwe-smackdown-results/61227-wwe-smackdown-results-42816-roman-reigns-vs-miz-headlines-manchester-final-build-payback-sunday/|website=wrestleview.com|accessdate=April 30, 2016}}</ref> On the May 2 episode of ''Raw'', Breeze defeated [[Goldust]] after interference by Truth.<ref>{{cite web|title=WWE Raw Results \u2013 5/2/16 (Live from St. Louis, fallout from Payback, Reigns and Usos vs. Styles, Gallows and Anderson)|url=http://www.wrestleview.com/wwe-wrestling-results/wwe-raw-results/61443-wwe-raw-results-5216-live-st-louis-fallout-payback-shane-stephanie-run-show-together/|website=wrestleview.com|accessdate=May 3, 2016}}</ref> On the May 12 episode of ''SmackDown'', Breeze and Truth would defeat Goldust and [[Fandango (wrestler)|Fandango]]. Following the match, a double turn occurred as Breeze and Fandango aligned and attacked Truth and Goldust.<ref>{{cite web|title=5/12 WWE Smackdown \u2013 Parks\u2019s Complete, Real-Time Report|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/site/2016/05/12/512-wwe-smackdown-parkss-complete-real-time-report/|website=PWTorch.com|accessdate=May 16, 2016}}</ref> On the May 16 episode of ''Raw'', Breeze and Fandango would defeat Truth and Goldust, and again on the May 26 episode of ''SmackDown''.<ref>{{cite web|title=WWE RAW RESULTS \u2013 5/16/16 (LIVE FROM GREENSBORO, THE USOS VS. LUKE GALLOWS AND KARL ANDERSON, EXTREME RULES)|url=http://www.wrestleview.com/wwe-wrestling-results/wwe-raw-results/62068-wwe-raw-results-51616-live-greensboro-usos-vs-luke-gallows-karl-anderson-extreme-rules-go-home/|website=WrestleView|accessdate=May 18, 2016}}</ref> Breezango however lost at [[Money in the Bank (2016)|Money in the Bank]], because they went into the match suffering from (kayfabe) severe burns, caused by Goldust adjusting the dial on their tanning machine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/site/2016/06/19/619-wwe-mitb-ppv-results-caldwells-ongoing-live-report/|title=6/19 WWE MITB PPV Results \u2013 Caldwell's Complete Live Report|last=Caldwell|first=James|publisher=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=June 19, 2016}}</ref> On July 19 at the [[2016 WWE draft]], Breezango was drafted to ''SmackDown''.<ref>{{cite web|title=2016 WWE Draft results: WWE officially ushers in New Era|url=http://www.wwe.com/2016-wwe-draft-results|publisher=WWE|accessdate=July 19, 2016}}</ref> On July 24 at the [[Battleground (2016)|Battleground]] pre-show, Breezango defeated [[The Usos]] (Jimmy and Jey) in a tag-team match.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Caldwell|first1=James|title=7/24 WWE Battleground Results \u2013 CALDWELL\u2019S Complete Report|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/site/2016/07/24/jcbattlegroundppvreport/|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|date=July 24, 2016|accessdate=July 25, 2016}}</ref> At [[SummerSlam (2016)|SummerSlam]], Breezango competed in a 12-man tag team match, where their team lost. They then entered the [[WWE SmackDown Tag Team Championship]] [[WWE tournaments|tournament]], where they were eliminated in the first round by [[American Alpha]].\n\nOn the November 8 episode of ''SmackDown'', Breezango defeated [[The Vaudevillains]] to qualify for Team SmackDown for the [[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Elimination tag team matches|10\u2013on\u201310 Survivor Series Tag Team Elimination match]] at [[Survivor Series (2016)|Survivor Series]], where they were defeated by Team Raw, with them being the first team eliminated from the match. During this time, Breezango would undergo a slight gimmick change, where they began to refer themselves as \"fashion police\". On April 2, 2017, on the [[WrestleMania 33]] kickoff show, Breeze, along with Fandango, both entered the [[Andr\u00e9 the Giant Memorial Trophy|Andr\u00e9 the Giant Memorial Battle Royal]], but were unsuccessful.\n\nOn the April 25 episode of ''SmackDown'', Breezango defeated [[The Ascension (professional wrestling)|The Ascension]] in a beat the clock challenge match, becoming the number one contenders for the SmackDown Tag Team Championship at [[Backlash (2017)|Backlash]]. During the feud, Breezango turned face in the process. At Backlash, Breezango unsuccessfully challenged [[The Usos]] for the SmackDown Tag Team Championship. On the May 23 episode of ''SmackDown'', after Fandango and Breeze defeated Jimmy Uso and Jey Uso in singles matches, Breezango challenged The Usos for the titles that same night, but were once again unsuccessful. At [[Money in the Bank (2017)]], Breezango defeated The Ascension. Over the next few months, Breezango competed on Smackdown in various matches. On the [[Survivor Series (2017)]] Kickoff, they lost to [[Kevin Owens and Sami Zayn]]. At [[Clash of Champions (2017)]], Breezango lost to [[Luke Harper and Erick Rowan|The Bludgeon Brothers]]. They would go on to lose a rematch on the December 26 episode of ''SmackDown''. On the January 2 episode of ''SmackDown'', Breezango had another match with The Bludgeon Brothers and The Ascension tried to save them, but got beat down. On the January 9 episode of ''SmackDown'', Breezango defeated [[Rusev (wrestler)|Rusev]] and [[Aiden English]]. On the [[Fastlane (2018)|Fastlane]] kickoff show, Breezango and [[Tye Dillinger]] defeated [[Mojo Rawley]], [[Chad Gable]], and [[Shelton Benjamin]] in a six-man tag team match. On the April 3 episode of ''SmackDown'', Breezango, Tye Dillinger and [[Zack Ryder]] defeated [[Baron Corbin]], [[Dolph Ziggler]], [[Mojo Rawley]] and [[Primo Col\u00f3n]] in an eight-man tag team match. On the [[WrestleMania 34]] kickoff show, Breeze competed in the 30-man battle royal for the Andr\u00e9 the Giant Memorial Trophy, which was won by [[Matt Hardy]].\n\nOn April 16, during the [[2018 WWE Superstar Shake-up]], Breezango was drafted to [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]] brand. That same night, they defeated [[Cesaro and Sheamus]]. At the [[WWE Greatest Royal Rumble|Greatest Royal Rumble]] event, Breeze entered the match but was unsuccessful after being eliminated by Mojo Rawley. On July 6, it was reported that Fandango had suffered a left labrum tear in his shoulder that would put him out of action for six months, which was why Breeze had been inactive. On the December 12 episode of ''NXT'', Breeze appeared as the surprise opponent for [[Ricochet (wrestler)|Ricochet]]'s [[NXT North American Championship]] match in a losing effort. On the December 17 episode of ''Raw'', Breeze accepted [[Dean Ambrose]]'s open challenge for the [[WWE Intercontinental Championship|Intercontinental Championship]], which he lost. At [[WrestleMania 35]], Breeze competed in the Andr\u00e9 the Giant Memorial Battle Royal which was won by [[Braun Strowman]]. On April 14 at [[WWE Worlds Collide]], Breeze defeated [[Roderick Strong]].\n\n====Return to NXT (2019\u2013present)====\nOn April 25, 2019, Breeze started appearing at NXT live events.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cagematch.net/?id=2&nr=9500&page=4|title=Matches \u00ab Tyler Breeze \u00ab Wrestlers Database \u00ab CAGEMATCH - The Internet Wrestling Database|website=www.cagematch.net}}</ref> On the May 22 episode of ''NXT'', Breeze returned to NXT television where he interrupted [[NXT North American Championship|NXT North American Champion]] [[Velveteen Dream]] and took a selfie with him, but then attacked him. It was announced that Breeze would face Velveteen Dream for the NXT North American Championship at [[NXT TakeOver: XXV]]. Ultimately, Breeze lost the match. On the July 31 episode of ''NXT'', Fandango returned after a one year absence to rescue Breeze from the Forgotten Sons ([[Wesley Blake]], [[Jaxson Ryker]] and [[Steve Cutler]]) thus reuniting Breezango. Breezango would begin a feud with the Forgotten Sons defeating them in tag team action as well as in a six-man tag action with [[Isaiah \"Swerve\" Scott]] as their partner. However, in December, Fandango was once again sidelined with an injury leaving Breeze as a singles competitor. On the January 10 episode of ''205 Live'', he made his brand debut defeating [[Tony Nese]]. The following week, he defeated [[Ariya Daivari]].\n\n== Other media ==\nClement made a cameo appearance in an updated video for [[The Chainsmokers]] song \"[[Selfie (song)|Selfie]]\" in 2014, but not on the original music video.<ref>{{cite web|title=How Tyler Breeze became a part of the music video for the internet's biggest viral song|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/wwenxt/tyler-breeze-selfie-chainsmokers|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=June 2, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2016, Clement started his own [[YouTube]] series called ''Shootin' the Breeze'', where Clement portrays his Breeze character answering fan questions. The first five episodes were released on Clement's own YouTube channel, before being moved to WWE's channel in March.<ref>{{cite web|title=Shootin' the Breeze with Tyler Breeze|url=https://m.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLqIVmFaHA8BpIOEGhKRIfodUuEDSqXFE6}}</ref> \n\nBreeze is a recurring guest on Xavier Woods' YouTube channel UpUpDownDown, where he goes by the nickname 'Prince Pretty'. In November 2019, Breeze defeated [[Alexa Bliss]] in a game of ''[[Saturday Night Slam Masters]]'' to win the UpUpDownDown Championship, immediately after Bliss had won the championship in the finals of a ''[[Brawlhalla]]'' tournament.<ref name=\"SURVIVOR SERIES UPUPDOWNDOWN CHAMPIONSHIP LIVESTREAM\"> https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=GaAwxREMYuQ</ref>\n\nBreeze made his [[video game]] debut in ''[[WWE 2K16]]''. He has continued to appear as a playable character in ''[[WWE 2K17]]'', ''[[WWE 2K18]]'' and ''[[WWE 2K19]]'', ''[[WWE 2K20]]''.\n\n== Personal life ==\nClement married Ashley Miller, better known as [[Audrey Marie]], in September 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heartbreakers.me/index.php?/topic/9357-former-nxt-diva-audrey-marie-marries-tyler-breeze/|title=Former NXT Diva Audrey Marie marries Tyler Breeze|website=Heartbreakers - A Cult Fandom Forum}}</ref> In May 2019, Clement and [[Tye Dillinger|Ronnie Arneill]] (best known as Tye Dillinger) opened a wrestling school in [[Apopka, Florida]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=126481|title=TYLER BREEZE, TYE DILLINGER OPENING WRESTLING SCHOOL - PWInsider.com|website=www.pwinsider.com}}</ref>\n\n== Championships and accomplishments and UNIVERSAL champion ==\n* '''NXT Championship Wrestling'''\n**[[FCW Florida Heavyweight Championship|FCW Florida World Heavyweight Championship]] ([[FCW Florida Heavyweight Championship#Title history|1 time]])<ref name=FCWChampions />\n** [[FCW Florida Tag Team Championship|FCW Florida World  Tag Team Championship]] ([[FCW Florida Tag Team Championship#Title history|1 time]]) \u2013 with [[Roman Reigns|Leakee]]<ref name=\"FCWChampions\"/>\n* '''[[Prairie Wrestling Alliance]]'''\n** PWA World heavyweight Tag Team Championship (1 time) \u2013 with Dan Myers<ref name=Cagematch />\n* '''''[[Pro Wrestling Illustrated]]'''''\n** Ranked No. 1 of the top 500 wrestlers in the [[Pro Wrestling Illustrated#PWI 500|PWI 500]] in 2015<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.profightdb.com/pwi-500/2015.html|title=Pro Wrestling Illustrated (PWI) 500 for 2015|accessdate=September 1, 2017|work=The Internet Wrestling Database}}</ref>                                       \n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category}}\n*{{wwe superstar|name = Tyler Breeze}}\n*{{facebook|TylerBreezePrincePretty}}\n*{{twitter}}\n*{{IMDb name|name = Mattias Clement}}\n* {{Professional wrestling profiles}}\n\n{{WWE personnel}}\n{{FCW Florida Heavyweight Championship}}\n{{FCW Florida Tag Team Championship}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Breeze, Tyler}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Canadian male professional wrestlers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Professional wrestlers from British Columbia]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Daytona Beach, Florida]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Penticton]]\n[[Category:American male professional wrestlers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Canadian professional wrestler|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2016}} \n{{Infobox professional wrestler\n|name        = Tyler Breeze\n|birthname = Mattias Clement\n|image       = Tyler Breeze April 2019.jpg\n|caption     = Breeze in April 2019\n|names       = {{Unbulleted list|Matt Clement<ref name=OWOW>{{cite web |url=http://www.onlineworldofwrestling.com/profiles/m/matt-clement.html|title=OWOW Profile|publisher=OWOW |accessdate=March 18, 2012}}</ref>|Mattias Wild<ref name=OWOW/>|Mike Dalton<ref name=FCWprofile>{{cite web|title=Mike Dalton \u2013 FCW profile, May '12|url=http://www.fcwwrestling.info/mikedalton1.html|publisher=[[Florida Championship Wrestling]]|accessdate=February 2, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120512111944/http://www.fcwwrestling.info/mikedalton1.html|archivedate=May 12, 2012|quote=height/weight: 6'1 / 195 lbs / hometown: Daytona Beach, FL / finishing move: Implant DDT}}</ref>|Mike McGrath<ref name=OWOW />|'''Tyler Breeze'''<ref name=WWEProfile>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/superstars/tylerbreeze|title=Tyler Breeze|work=[[WWE]]|accessdate=March 23, 2016}}</ref>}}\n|height      = {{height|ft=6|in=0}}<ref name=WWEProfile/>\n|weight      = {{convert|204|lb|kg|abbr=on}}<ref name=WWEProfile/>\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1988|1|19}} <ref name=OWOW /> \n|birth_place = [[Penticton|Penticton, British Columbia]], [[Canada]]\n|billed      = [[Daytona Beach, Florida]]<ref name=FCWprofile/><br />Penticton, British Columbia<ref name=FCWprofileOlder/><br>'''Seasonal residences'''<ref name=\"NXT15Jan2014\">{{cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_75711.shtml|title=James's WWE NXT Report 1/15|author=James, Justin|publisher=[[Wade Keller|Pro Wrestling Torch]]|work=[[Wade Keller|PWTorch.com]]|date=January 16, 2014|accessdate=January 26, 2014|quote=Adrian is facing Tyler Breeze, who is now being billed as from his \"seasonal residency\" in Brazil.}}</ref> \n|trainer     = [[Lance Storm]]<ref name=FCWprofileOlder/> \n|debut       = 2007<ref name=OWOW /> \n|retired     = \n}}\n'''Mattias Clement''' (born January 19, 1988) is a Canadian [[Professional wrestling|professional wrestler]] currently signed to [[WWE]], performing on the [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]] and [[205 Live]] brands under the [[ring name]] '''Tyler Breeze'''. \n\nFrom 2010 to 2012 Clement performed under the name '''Mike Dalton''' in WWE's [[Farm team#professional wrestling|developmental territory]] [[Florida Championship Wrestling]] (FCW). While in FCW he won the [[FCW Florida Heavyweight Championship]] and the [[FCW Florida Tag Team Championship]].\n\nIn 2013, he transitioned to NXT and came up with the \"Tyler Breeze\" character, a narcissistic \"pretty boy\" obsessed with taking [[selfie]]s of himself, even during matches. In 2015, Clement was promoted to WWE's main roster, where he would later team up with [[Fandango (wrestler)|Fandango]] to form a team known as \"Breezango\" and later on as \"The Fashion Police\" after the two began appearing in a number of comedic skits known as \"the Fashion Files\". In 2019 he returned to NXT as a full-time performer.\n\nClement is married to professional wrestler [[Audrey Marie]] and runs a wrestling school in Florida with [[Shawn Spears]].\n\n==Early life==\nClement was born on January 19, 1988<ref name=FCWprofileOlder>{{cite web|title=Mike Dalton \u2013 FCW profile, Feb '11|url=http://www.fcwwrestling.info/mikedalton1.html|publisher=[[Florida Championship Wrestling]]|accessdate=February 2, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120512111944/http://www.fcwwrestling.info/mikedalton1.html|archivedate=May 12, 2012 |quote=hometown: Penticton, BC, Canada / birthday: January 19th / At 23 years old (archived Feb '11), Dalton has youth on his side...}}</ref> in [[Penticton|Penticton, British Columbia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.profightdb.com/wrestlers/tyler-breeze-6734.html|title=Tyler Breeze: Profile & Match Listing|website=profightdb}}</ref> He trained under former [[Extreme Championship Wrestling|ECW]], [[WCW]] and [[WWE]] pro wrestler [[Lance Storm]] at Storm's academy in [[Calgary]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stormwrestling.com/academy/swaphoto.html|title=Storm Wrestling Academy|website=www.stormwrestling.com}}</ref>\n\n== Professional wrestling career ==\n\n=== Early career (2007\u20132010) ===\nClement made his debut for Power Zone Wrestling in 2007 under the [[ring name]] '''Mattias Wild'''.<ref name=OWOW /> His first match was a victory over Rage O'Riley on April 25, 2007.<ref name=OWOW /> In 2008, Clement began wrestling for [[Elite Canadian Championship Wrestling|NWA Extreme Canadian Championship Wrestling]] (ECCW).<ref name=OWOW /> While wrestling for ECCW, Clement was trained by [[Lance Storm]] in [[Calgary, Alberta]].<ref name=OWOW /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stormwrestling.com/academy/wwesignings.html|title=Storm Alumni network|author=Lance Storm|authorlink=Lance Storm|publisher=Stormacademy |accessdate=March 18, 2012}}</ref> On May 2, Clement won a match against Alex Plexis to qualify for the first round of the 2009 [[ECCW Pacific Cup|Pacific Cup]]; he then lost in the first round to [[Billy Suede]] on June 6, 2009.<ref name=OWOW /> On September 5, 2009, he lost a [[tag team match]] with Dan Myers against the team of \"The Icons\" Jamie Diaz and Nick Price in a first round match for the [[ECCW Tag Team Championship]].<ref name=OWOW /> The teams then began a feud, with Price and Diaz coming out on top on most occasions.<ref name=OWOW /> Clement then worked for [[Prairie Wrestling Alliance]] in 2010, returning to ECCW for a last match on September 11, 2010, which he lost to Billy Suede.<ref name=OWOW /><ref name=Cagematch>{{cite web|url=http://www.cagematch.net/?id=2&nr=9500&page=4|title=Dalton Cagematch Profile|author=|date=|work=|publisher=Cagematch|accessdate=March 26, 2012}}</ref>\n\n=== World Wrestling Entertainment/WWE ===\n==== Developmental territories (2010\u20132015) ====\nAfter signing with [[WWE|World Wrestling Entertainment]] (WWE), Clement made his debut for WWE's [[Farm team#Professional wrestling|developmental territory]] [[Florida Championship Wrestling]] (FCW) on December 2, 2010, at a live event as '''Matt Clement''', where he defeated [[Big E (wrestler)|Big E Langston]], [[Darren Young]], [[Roman Reigns|Leakee]] and 2 others.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cagematch.net/?id=1&nr=58305 |title=02.12.2010 |website=CageMatch |quote=Buck Dixon, Chimaera, Husky Harris, Kenny Li & Matt Clements (w/Michael McGillicutty) defeat Big E. Langston, Darren Young, James Bronson, Kevin Hackman & Roman Leakee}}</ref> The following month he was called '''Mike McGrath''',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cagematch.net/?id=1&nr=61472 |date=January 8, 2011 |title=08.01.2011 |website=CageMatch}}</ref> which lasted 3 months, only to be changed again to '''Mike Dalton''' in April 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cagematch.net/?id=1&nr=62402 |date=April 14, 2011 |title=14.04.2011 |website=CageMatch}}</ref> Dalton made his television debut on the July 17, 2011 episode of ''FCW TV'' in a loss to [[Rusev (wrestler)|Alexander Rusev]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|title=Florida Championship Wrestling Television Report: All FCW Champions In Action; Johnny Curtis Gets Another Shot At The Fcw Title; Alexander Rusev Makes His Television Debut|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/59929/florida-championship-wrestling-television-report-all-fcw-champions-in-action-johnny-curtis-gets-another-shot-at-the-fcw-title-alexander-rusev-makes-his-television-debut.html?p=1|work=PWInsider|accessdate=July 26, 2013}}</ref> He earned another win in FCW on November 17, 2011, against [[Alex Koslov|Peter Orlov]].<ref name=Cagematch /> On December 15, Dalton won a battle royal to be named the number-one contender to the [[FCW Florida Heavyweight Championship]].<ref name=Cagematch /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wrestling-news.net/spoilers-taping-results-airing-7/1915/|title=Spoilers: FCW Taping Results Airing January 22nd, 2012|publisher=Wrestling News|accessdate=March 18, 2012}} {{unreliable source?|failed=y|date=June 2012}}</ref> He challenged [[Adam Rose|Leo Kruger]], but lost the match.<ref name=Cagematch /> Dalton won the FCW Heavyweight Championship on February 2, 2012, when he defeated Kruger.<ref name=FCWChampions>{{cite web|url=http://www.fcwwrestling.info/champions.html|title=FCW Champions|publisher=[[Florida Championship Wrestling]]|accessdate=March 26, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110219131349/http://www.fcwwrestling.info/champions.html|archivedate=February 19, 2011|df=mdy-all}}</ref> His reign lasted 21 days and he lost the rematch and the title to Kruger.<ref name=FCWChampions /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/96-wwe/24060-two-title-changes-at-tonights-fcw-tapings|title=Two title changes at tonight's FCW tapings|last=Meltzer|first=Dave|authorlink=Dave Meltzer|work=[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]|date=February 2, 2012|accessdate=February 4, 2012}}</ref>\n\nWhen WWE [[Rebranding|rebranded]] FCW into [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT Wrestling]],<ref name=\"FCWtoNXT\">{{cite web|url=http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/118-daily-updates/27030-wwe-news-fcw-name-being-phased-out|title= WWE News: FCW name being phased out|accessdate=August 14, 2012|publisher=Wrestling Observer}}</ref> Dalton debuted as an [[Job (professional wrestling)|enhancement talent]] on the June 20, 2012, episode of rebooted ''[[WWE NXT|NXT]]'' show, where he teamed with [[Juice Robinson|CJ Parker]] and lost to [[The Ascension (professional wrestling)|The Ascension]] ([[Bram (wrestler)|Kenneth Cameron]] and [[Konnor (wrestler)|Conor O'Brian]]).<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 6/20 \u2013 Week 1 of new season: Kidd vs. McGillicutty main event, Ross & Regal on commentary|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_62864.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=July 14, 2012}}</ref> Dalton got his first victory when he teamed with [[Jason Jordan]] and defeated the team of [[Sin Cara|Hunico]] and [[Tanga Loa|Camacho]] on August 1<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT RESULTS 8/1: NXT Title tournament begins with Rollins, Steamboat, McIntyre|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_64115.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=August 9, 2012}}</ref> but lost in a rematch against the two a few weeks later.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 8/29 \u2013 Week 11: First NXT champion crowned in big-match setting|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_64831.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=September 8, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn the beginning of 2013, seeing that Dalton's character hadn't receive much of the fans' attention, WWE officials informed him that in order to remain with WWE he should get a new character.<ref name=\"E60\">''[[E:60]] Behind the Curtain'' [[ESPN]] (May 5, 2015)</ref> On the July 24 episode of ''NXT'', Clement re\u2013debuted with his new [[Heel (professional wrestling)|heel]] [[gimmick (professional wrestling)|gimmick]], as '''Tyler Breeze''', a narcissistic \"pretty boy\" obsessed with taking [[selfie]]s, even during matches;<ref name=ReDebuting>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT RESULTS 7/24: First NXT Women's champion crowned & Triple H makes appearance, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_72241.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=July 26, 2013}}</ref><ref name=Breeze>{{cite web|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|title=WWE NXT REPORT: UNITED STATES TITLE ON THE LINE; NXT TITLE ON THE LINE; DANCE SUPREMACY IN NXT ON THE LINE; TYLER BREEZE IS TYLER BREEZE; AND MORE|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/79480/wwe-nxt-report-united-states-title-on-the-line-nxt-title-on-the-line-dance-supremacy-in-nxt-on-the-line-tyler-breeze-is-tyler-breeze-and-more.html?p=1|accessdate=August 9, 2013|publisher=PWInsider}}</ref> and later was revealed that Clement himself came up with the character, with [[Triple H]] giving him the suggestion of using an [[iPhone]] to take pictures as a way to make the character more modern.<ref name=\"E60\"/> Soon after, Breeze started a [[Feud (professional wrestling)|feud]] with CJ Parker, after repeatedly being \"[[photobomb]]ed\" by Parker.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT RESULTS 8/21 & 8/28 & 9/4: Cesaro vs. Sami Zayn MOTY contender, A.J. Lee title defense, Summer Rae, Swagger, new feuds & developments|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_73169.shtml#.VlC_enbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=September 5, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 9/11: Paige defends Women's Title, Xavier Woods main event, Overall Reax to weak episode|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_73296.shtml#.VlC_f3bhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=September 13, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT RESULTS 9/18: Zayn/Generico vs. Hawkins, big eight-man tag main event, Bo Dallas Hotline, more|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_73441.shtml#.VlC_f3bhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=September 21, 2013}}</ref> After the two were put in a [[Professional wrestling tag team match types|tag team match]] against [[Enzo and Cass|Enzo Amore and Colin Cassady]], which they lost after Parker refused to tag in Breeze,<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 9/25 - Week 65: Triple H makes \"big announcement,\" Ohno/Hero returns, Zayn/Generico in action, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_73578.shtml#.VlC_g3bhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=September 27, 2013}}</ref> a match between the two took place on the October 16 episode of ''NXT'', which Breeze won.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 10/16: Dallas vs. Zayn/Generico for NXT Title, plus Tag Title match, Divas tag, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_73974.shtml#.VlDBDnbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=October 17, 2013}}</ref> Two weeks later, Parker defeated Breeze in a rematch, and ended their feud.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT RESULTS 10/30 - Week 70: Paige vs. Summer Rae, WWE prospects in action, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_74295.shtml#.VlDBFHbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=November 1, 2013}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Tyler Breeze WM31Axxess.jpg|thumb|right|260px|Breeze performing his signature pose]]\nIn December, Breeze helped [[Bo Dallas]] retain the [[NXT Championship]] during a [[Professional wrestling match types#Lumberjack match|lumberjack match]] against [[Neville (wrestler)|Adrian Neville]],<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=James's WWE NXT report 12/18 \u2013 Week 77: NXT Title match, Davey Richards & Eddie Edwards in a WWE ring, Kidd & Zayn, Divas champ in action, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_75204.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=December 19, 2013}}</ref> which resulted a match between the two on the January 15, 2014, episode of ''NXT'', where Neville was victorious.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES' WWE NXT REPORT 1/8 - Week 80: NXT tag champs in action, Summer Rae, Tyson Kidd, Rusev, Overall Reax |url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_75568.shtml#.VlDNgnbhDIV |work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=January 9, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 1/15 - Week 81 |url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_75711.shtml#.VlDNi3bhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=January 16, 2014}}</ref> Breeze retorted later that Neville was not good-looking, mocking his nickname.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sagGAKuuSBM&t=2m |title=Breeze Promo |date=January 28, 2014 |first=Tyler |last=Breeze |quote=The Man That Gravity Forgot... more like... The Man That Mother Nature Forgot To Make Good-Looking}}</ref> The next month, in a rematch, Neville once again defeated Breeze.<ref>{{cite web |last=James |first=Justin |title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 2/19 - Week 86: Final hype for next week's \"NXT Arrival,\" Cesaro-Zayn sit-down interview, NXT tag champs, Emma vs. Summer Rae; Overall Reax |url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_76474.shtml |work=Pro Wrestling Torch |date=February 19, 2014 |access-date=December 11, 2015}}</ref> On February 27, at [[NXT Arrival]], Breeze was scheduled to face [[Xavier Woods]], but both men were attacked by Alexander Rusev, rendering the match a no contest.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT \"ARRIVAL\" REPORT 2/27 - Week 87: Complete real-time coverage of WWE Network special, including all NXT Titles on the line, plus Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_76685.shtml#.VlDO4HbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=February 27, 2014}}</ref> Throughout March, Breeze continued his feud with Woods, by attacking him before a match with Rusev,<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 3/13 - Week 89: Tag champs & Women's champ in action, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_76999.shtml#.VlDO53bhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=March 13, 2014}}</ref> before the two faced each other in a match, which Breeze won.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 3/27: Neville defends NXT Title vs. Dallas, Bret Hart cameo, Yoshi, Xavier, Charlotte, more|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_77299.shtml#.VlDRHHbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=March 27, 2014}}</ref> On the May 8 episode of ''NXT'', Breeze participated in a 20-man [[Professional wrestling battle royal|battle royal]], for a shot at the NXT Championship, and was involved in a three-way tie.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=James's WWE NXT report 5/8 \u2013 Week 97: Battle Royal for NXT Title shot, Women's Title tournament continues, Triple H appearance, Exotic Express; Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_78282.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=May 20, 2014}}</ref> As a result, Breeze faced the other two winners, [[Sami Zayn]] and [[Tyson Kidd]] in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|triple\u2013threat match]] on the following week, which Kidd won.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=James's WWE NXT report 5/15 \u2013 Week 98: NXT Title #1 contender match, Women's Title tourney continues; Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_78422.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=May 20, 2014}}</ref> On May 29, at [[NXT TakeOver]], Breeze defeated Sami Zayn in another number one contender's match<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 5/22 - Week 99: Final hype for Take-Over Live Special, Bo Dallas written off, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_78577.shtml#.VlDRdXbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=May 22, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=James's WWE NXT TakeOver report 5/29: Complete \"virtual-time\" coverage of live special on WWE Network|url=http://pwtorch.com/atman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_78704.shtml|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=June 2, 2014}}{{Dead link|date=July 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=no }}</ref> but in mid\u2013June he suffered a broken finger, which kept him out of action for a month.<ref>{{cite web|title=WWE News: NXT standout Tyler Breeze provides an update on his finger injury|url=http://prowrestling.net/article.php?WWE-News-NXT-standout-Tyler-Breeze-provides-an-update-on-his-finger-injury-38042|work=Pro Wrestling.Net|accessdate=July 17, 2014}}</ref> Breeze returned on the July 24 episode of ''NXT'', defeating [[Mojo Rawley]]<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 7/24 - Week 108: Charlotte defends NXT Women's Title, Rusev faces NXT Champ; Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_79812.shtml#.VlDVJXbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=July 25, 2014}}</ref> and received his title match against champion Adrian Neville on the August 14 episode of ''NXT'', but was unsuccessful after Kidd interfered and caused a disqualification.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 8/14 - Week 111: Neville defends NXT Title vs. Breeze, tournament continues, #1 contender to Women's Title; Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_80200.shtml#.VlDVMHbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=August 14, 2014}}</ref> This led to a match between Breeze and Kidd on the following week, which Kidd won, when Breeze counted himself out.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 8/21 - Week 112: Tag Tournament continues, Women's champ Charlotte in action, Triple H makes announcement for \"Takeover 2,\" Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_80354.shtml#.VlDVM3bhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=August 21, 2014}}</ref> On September 11, Breeze, along with Zayn and Kidd, once again challenged unsuccessfully for the title at [[NXT TakeOver: Fatal 4-Way]].<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT \"TAKEOVER FATAL4WAY\" REPORT 9/11: Neville defends NXT Title in big main event, new NXT Tag Champs, KENTA debuts, Charlotte defends Women's Title, more|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_80704.shtml#.VlDWUHbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=September 11, 2014}}</ref> Prior to this, Breeze made his main roster debut on the September 8 episode of ''[[WWE Raw|Raw]]'', teaming with Kidd in a match against Neville and Zayn, to hype their title match.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/raw/2014-09-08/wwe-raw-results-26639612/page-6|title=WWE Raw results, September 8, 2014: The Authority contains Roman Reigns, Bella brawl engulfs Jerry Springer and NXT Superstars 'take over' Raw|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=September 8, 2014}}</ref> Throughout the next months, Breeze competed in various matches, but was not involved in any feud.<ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 9/25 - Week 119: Lucha Dragons defend NXT Tag Titles, Itami vs. Ascension, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_80933.shtml#.VlDXSHbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=September 24, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT RESULTS 10/9: Titus O'Neil gets a real, actual main event against Sami Zayn and not a Bunny, plus Itami/KENTA, Becky Lynch, more; plus Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_81189.shtml#.VlDXTXbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=October 9, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 10/23: Neville defends NXT Title against Titus O'Neil, Tyler Breeze, Ascension, more; Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_81430.shtml#.VlDYEXbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=October 24, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT RESULTS 11/6: Prince Devitt/Finn Balor debuts, Zayn vs. Breeze show-stealer, Charlotte; Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_81673.shtml#.VlDXvHbhDIU|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=November 6, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=James|first=Justin|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 11/27 - Week 128: Balor/Devitt in main event, latest Kevin Steen/Owens vignette, Overall Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_82032.shtml#.VlDXZHbhDIV|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=November 30, 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn the December 18 episode of ''NXT'', a [[mobile phone|cell phone]] [[glossary of professional wrestling terms#Vignette|vignette]] from Breeze aired, claiming that he was taking a short break from NXT to model overseas.<ref name=\"WWE NXT Results - 12/18/14 (Neville vs. Owens)\">{{cite web|last1=Namako|first1=Jason|title=WWE NXT Results - 12/18/14 (Neville vs. Owens)|url=http://www.wrestleview.com/wwe-news/52221-wwe-nxt-results-12-18-14-neville-vs-owens|website=wrestleview.com|publisher=WrestleView|accessdate=December 18, 2014}}</ref> He returned on the January 8, 2015 episode of ''NXT'', defeating the debuting [[Chad Gable]].<ref name=\"WWE NXT results - Jan. 8, 2015: Sami Zayn returns, Lucha Dragons and Vaudevillains clash for Tag Team Titles\">{{cite web|last1=Melok|first1=Bobby|title=WWE NXT results - Jan. 8, 2015: Sami Zayn returns, Lucha Dragons and Vaudevillains clash for Tag Team Titles|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/wwenxt/2015-01-08/wwe-nxt-results-2015-01-05-26985961|website=wwe.com|accessdate=January 9, 2015}}</ref> On the January 21 episode of ''NXT'', Breeze was defeated by [[Hideo Itami]] in a first round match of a tournament to determine the new number one contender for the NXT Championship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wrestleview.com/wwe-news/52854-wwe-nxt-results-1-21-15-itami-vs-breeze|title=WWE NXT RESULTS - 1/21/15 (ITAMI VS. BREEZE)|publisher=WrestleView|accessdate=January 26, 2015}}</ref> In a rematch at [[NXT TakeOver: Rival]], on February 11, Itami again defeated Breeze.<ref>{{cite web|title=WWE NXT Takeover report 2/11: Zayn vs. Owens NXT Title match, Women's Title semi-main event, Neville-Balor; Reax|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_83281.shtml|publisher=Pro Wrestling Torch|last=James|first=Justin|accessdate=February 13, 2015}}</ref> Breeze's rivalry with Itami continued and the two along with [[Finn B\u00e1lor]] were scheduled for a triple\u2013threat number one contender's match at [[NXT TakeOver: Unstoppable]], on May 20, however, Itami was attacked in the parking lot, and the match was turned into a one on one between Breeze and B\u00e1lor, which B\u00e1lor won.<ref name=NXTUnstopable>{{cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_85123.shtml|title=WWE NXT \"TakeOver: Unstoppable\" report 5/20: Owens vs. Zayn for the NXT Title ends in wild fashion with a major debut of Samoa Joe, plus spectacular NXT Women's Title match, more; Overall Reax|work=PWTorch.com|accessdate=May 21, 2014|first1=Justin|last1=James}}</ref><ref name=F4Unstoppable>{{cite web | url=http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/96-wwe-news/42639-wwe-nxt-takeover-unstoppable-results-a-live-coverage-kevin-owens-vs-sami-zayn | title=WWE NXT TakeOver Unstoppable results & live coverage: Kevin Owens vs. Sami Zayn, surprise debut | date=May 20, 2015 | accessdate=August 26, 2015 | first=Dave | last=Meltzer | work=Wrestling Observer Figure Four Online}}</ref> During the tapings of ''NXT'', on July 16, [[William Regal]] scheduled Breeze to wrestle [[Jushin Thunder Liger]] at [[NXT TakeOver: Brooklyn]], on August 22.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/WWE_News_3/article_86266.shtml|title=WWE NXT news: Jushin Liger announced for \"Takeover\" special, Balor-Owens, Samoa Joe, Charlotte, more notes from Thursday's TV taping|date=July 16, 2015|accessdate=July 17, 2015|work=Pro Wrestling Torch}}</ref> Breeze called himself the \"Face of the Rising Sun\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6oc8bVXEnKg&t=44 |title=Breeze promises to vanquish Jushin \u201cThunder\u201d Liger at TakeOver: WWE.com Exclusive, Aug. 5, 2015 |date=August 5, 2015 |first=Tyler |last=Breeze |quote=Finn Balor might have won the NXT Championship in Tokyo, but I am the face of the rising sun.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aFoUGF5nvSU&t=55 |title=Tyler Breeze addresses accusations of arrogance: WWE.com Exclusive, Aug. 19, 2015 |date=August 18, 2015 |first=Tyler |last=Breeze |quote=What I like to call it is confidence because I am slowly becoming the face of the rising sun, thanks to Mister Thunder Liger, so you know what? Domo Ari...Gorgeous.}}</ref> until Liger won.<ref name=\"brooklyn\">{{cite web |url=http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/96-wwe-news/44186-wwe-nxt-takeover-live-results-a-main-card-finn-balor-vs-kevin-owens-sasha-banks-vs-bayley-samoa-joe-jushin-qthunderq-liger |title=WWE NXT TakeOver live results & main card |last=Witner |first=Emerson |website=[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]] |date=August 22, 2015 |accessdate=August 22, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150823140341/http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/96-wwe-news/44186-wwe-nxt-takeover-live-results-a-main-card-finn-balor-vs-kevin-owens-sasha-banks-vs-bayley-samoa-joe-jushin-qthunderq-liger |archive-date=August 23, 2015 |quote=Liger hit it on the third try and won.}}</ref> Breeze then entered the ''[[Dusty Rhodes Tag Team Classic]]'' tournament, where he was paired with [[Bull Dempsey]]. The two were eliminated from the tournament by [[Tommaso Ciampa]] [[DIY (professional wrestling)|and]] [[Johnny Gargano]] on the September 9 episode of ''NXT'' when Dempsey got pinned.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_87409.shtml#.VhqPwvntmko|title=JAMES'S WWE NXT REPORT 9/9 - Week 179: Finn Balor & Samoa Joe vs. Lucha Dragons, Ciampa & Gargano also in Dusty Tag Classic match, more; Overall Reax|author=Justin James|website=[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]|date=September 9, 2015|accessdate=September 9, 2015}}</ref> This led to a match between the two on the September 23 episode of ''NXT'', which Breeze won.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwenxtreport/article_87669.shtml|title=WWE NXT results 9/23: Vaudevillains defend NXT Tag Titles, Kana/Asuka formally introduced, Breeze, Eva Marie, more|date=September 23, 2015|accessdate=September 30, 2015|work=Pro Wrestling Torch}}</ref> On October 7, at [[NXT TakeOver: Respect]], Breeze competed in a match against [[Apollo Crews]], which he would lose.<ref name=\"NXTRespect\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=97087&p=3|title=WWE NXT TAKEOVER RESPECT REPORT: SASHA BANKS AND BAYLEY GO 30 MINUTES, THE FIRST DUSTY RHODES TAG TEAM CLASSIC WINNERS CROWNED, ASUKA MAKES HER NXT IN RING DEBUT (POOR DANA), AND MORE|author=Trionfo, Richard|website=PWInsider|date=October 7, 2015|accessdate=October 7, 2015}}</ref> It would mark his final match at NXT, as Breeze was called up to the main roster after the event by Triple H.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ww1.prowrestlingreports.com/?sub1=a109272c-88d9-11e9-8e65-b2a089964cd9|title=prowrestlingreports.com\u00a0-\u00a0Diese Website steht zum Verkauf!\u00a0-\u00a0Informationen zum Thema prowrestlingreports.|website=ww1.prowrestlingreports.com}}</ref>\n\n==== Singles main roster run (2015\u20132016) ====\n[[File:Tyler Breeze April 2016.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Breeze in April 2016]]\nOn the October 22, 2015 episode of ''[[WWE SmackDown|SmackDown]]'', Breeze was promoted to WWE's main roster, appearing during a [[The Miz|Miz TV]] segment, after being introduced by [[Summer Rae]], and attacked [[Dolph Ziggler]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/index.php/2015/10/22/1022-wwe-smackdown-report-by-greg-parks/|title=10/22 WWE Smackdown Report by Greg Parks|author=Parks, Greg|website=Pro Wrestling Torch|date=October 22, 2015|accessdate=October 22, 2015}}</ref> On the November 9 episode of ''[[WWE Raw|Raw]]'', Breeze made his in\u2013ring debut, losing to [[Dean Ambrose]] in a first round match from the [[WWE Championship|WWE World Heavyweight Championship]] [[Survivor Series (2015)#WWE World Heavyweight Championship tournament|tournament]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/index.php/2015/11/09/119-wwe-raw-results-caldwells-ongoing-live-report/|title=11/9 WWE Raw Results \u2013 CALDWELL\u2019S Complete Live Report|author=Caldwell, James|website=Pro Wrestling Torch|date=November 9, 2015|accessdate=November 9, 2015}}</ref> Throughout November, Breeze continued his [[Feud (professional wrestling)|feud]] with Ziggler,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/index.php/2015/11/16/1116-wwe-raw-caldwells-live-report-on-pre-survivor-series-show/|title=11/16 WWE Raw Results: CALDWELL\u2019S Complete Live Report|author=Caldwell, James|website=Pro Wrestling Torch|date=November 16, 2015|accessdate=November 16, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/site/2015/11/19/1119-smackdown-parkss-complete-live-report/|title=11/19 Smackdown: Parks\u2019s Complete Live Report|author=Parks, Greg|website=Pro Wrestling Torch|date=November 19, 2015|accessdate=November 19, 2015}}</ref> resulting in a match at [[Survivor Series (2015)|Survivor Series]], which Breeze won.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/survivorseries/2015/dolph-ziggler-tyler-breeze-28201142|title=Dolph Ziggler vs. Tyler Breeze|author=Clapp, John|website=WWE.com|date=November 19, 2015|accessdate=November 19, 2015}}</ref> However, Ziggler defeated Breeze on ''Raw''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/raw/2015-11-30/wwe-raw-results-28306413/page-2|title=WWE Raw results, Nov. 30, 2015: Sheamus forms a League of Nations, Charlotte channels Flair and The Dudleys call in 'family' to battle the Wyatts|author=Benigno, Anthony|website=[[WWE]]|date=November 30, 2015|accessdate=December 11, 2015}}</ref> and ''SmackDown'', in two rematches, to officially end their feud.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/smackdown/2015-12-10/results-december-10-2015-28349401/page-2|title=Shows|website=WWE}}</ref> After competing in various matches, Breeze and Summer Rae amicably went their separate ways on the December 31 episode of ''SmackDown''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/videos/goldust-vs-tyler-breeze-smackdown-december-31-2015|title=Goldust vs. Tyler Breeze: SmackDown, December 31, 2015|publisher=|via=www.wwe.com}}</ref>\n\n{{Quote box\n| quote = \"Zack Ryder def. Tyler Breeze by pinfall - Yes, you read that correctly. Breeze\u2019s descent into [[Job (professional wrestling)|jobber]] hell continues; boy, does that season finale of Breaking Ground look ill-judged now\".\n| source = ''[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]'' writer Alan O'Brien commenting on an episode of ''[[WWE Main Event|Main Event]]'' in March 2016<ref>{{cite web|title=A deep look into what has brought WWE to where they are now, mistakes that were made (even as recently as Monday) & what needs to happen now|url=http://www.f4wonline.com/wwe-news/wwe-main-event-results-rich-brennan-goes-full-striker-natalya-warms-roadblock-209241|accessdate=13 March 2016|website=f4wonline.com}}</ref>\n| align = right\n| width = 25%\n}}\nStarting on the January 11, 2016 episode of ''Raw'', Breeze went on a winless streak for over 20 televised matches, including losing to the likes of [[Zack Ryder]] and [[Jack Swagger]] on ''[[WWE Main Event|Main Event]]'' or ''[[WWE Superstars|Superstars]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.profightdb.com/wrestlers/tyler-breeze-6734.html?res=2000|title=Tyler Breeze: Profile & Match Listing - Internet Wrestling Database (IWD)|website=www.profightdb.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cagematch.net//?id=2&nr=9500&view=&page=4&showtype=TV-Show%7CPay+Per+View|title=Matches \u00ab Tyler Breeze \u00ab Wrestlers Database \u00ab CAGEMATCH - The Internet Wrestling Database|website=www.cagematch.net}}</ref><!-- WINLESS STREAK BECAUSE 1/11 RAW WAS A NO CONTEST. DO NOT REPORT FORTY NINE LOSSES AS THIS INCLUDES HOUSE SHOWS, WHICH ARE ALMOST ALWAYS NOT NOTABLE AND WITHOUT STORYLINE DEVELOPMENTS. HEELS ALSO TEND TO LOSE AT HOUSE SHOWS. ONLY NOTE TELEVISED MATCHES --> At [[Royal Rumble (2016)|Royal Rumble]], Breeze was eliminated within two minutes in his first [[Royal Rumble#match|Royal Rumble match]] by [[Roman Reigns]] and [[A.J. Styles|AJ Styles]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Caldwell|first1=James|title=1/24 Royal Rumble PPV Results \u2013 CALDWELL\u2019S Complete Live Report |url=http://www.pwtorch.com/site/2016/01/24/caldwell2016rumblereport/|accessdate=January 25, 2016}}</ref> On the February 15 episode of ''Raw'', Breeze competed in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|five way]] match against Dean Ambrose, [[Kevin Owens]], [[Cody Rhodes|Stardust]] and Dolph Ziggler for Ambrose's [[WWE Intercontinental Championship]], where Breeze was pinned by Owens. At [[WrestleMania 32]], Breeze competed in the [[Andr\u00e9 the Giant Memorial Trophy]], where he was eliminated by [[Mark Henry]].\n\n====Teaming with Fandango (2016\u20132019)====\n{{More citations needed section|date=February 2019}}\nOn the April 28 episode of ''SmackDown'', Breeze formed an alliance with [[Ron Killings|R-Truth]].<ref>{{cite web|title=WWE SmackDown Results \u2013 4/28/16 (Roman Reigns vs. The Miz headlines in Manchester, final build for Payback on Sunday)|url=http://www.wrestleview.com/wwe-wrestling-results/wwe-smackdown-results/61227-wwe-smackdown-results-42816-roman-reigns-vs-miz-headlines-manchester-final-build-payback-sunday/|website=wrestleview.com|accessdate=April 30, 2016}}</ref> On the May 2 episode of ''Raw'', Breeze defeated [[Goldust]] after interference by Truth.<ref>{{cite web|title=WWE Raw Results \u2013 5/2/16 (Live from St. Louis, fallout from Payback, Reigns and Usos vs. Styles, Gallows and Anderson)|url=http://www.wrestleview.com/wwe-wrestling-results/wwe-raw-results/61443-wwe-raw-results-5216-live-st-louis-fallout-payback-shane-stephanie-run-show-together/|website=wrestleview.com|accessdate=May 3, 2016}}</ref> On the May 12 episode of ''SmackDown'', Breeze and Truth would defeat Goldust and [[Fandango (wrestler)|Fandango]]. Following the match, a double turn occurred as Breeze and Fandango aligned and attacked Truth and Goldust.<ref>{{cite web|title=5/12 WWE Smackdown \u2013 Parks\u2019s Complete, Real-Time Report|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/site/2016/05/12/512-wwe-smackdown-parkss-complete-real-time-report/|website=PWTorch.com|accessdate=May 16, 2016}}</ref> On the May 16 episode of ''Raw'', Breeze and Fandango would defeat Truth and Goldust, and again on the May 26 episode of ''SmackDown''.<ref>{{cite web|title=WWE RAW RESULTS \u2013 5/16/16 (LIVE FROM GREENSBORO, THE USOS VS. LUKE GALLOWS AND KARL ANDERSON, EXTREME RULES)|url=http://www.wrestleview.com/wwe-wrestling-results/wwe-raw-results/62068-wwe-raw-results-51616-live-greensboro-usos-vs-luke-gallows-karl-anderson-extreme-rules-go-home/|website=WrestleView|accessdate=May 18, 2016}}</ref> Breezango however lost at [[Money in the Bank (2016)|Money in the Bank]], because they went into the match suffering from (kayfabe) severe burns, caused by Goldust adjusting the dial on their tanning machine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/site/2016/06/19/619-wwe-mitb-ppv-results-caldwells-ongoing-live-report/|title=6/19 WWE MITB PPV Results \u2013 Caldwell's Complete Live Report|last=Caldwell|first=James|publisher=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=June 19, 2016}}</ref> On July 19 at the [[2016 WWE draft]], Breezango was drafted to ''SmackDown''.<ref>{{cite web|title=2016 WWE Draft results: WWE officially ushers in New Era|url=http://www.wwe.com/2016-wwe-draft-results|publisher=WWE|accessdate=July 19, 2016}}</ref> On July 24 at the [[Battleground (2016)|Battleground]] pre-show, Breezango defeated [[The Usos]] (Jimmy and Jey) in a tag-team match.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Caldwell|first1=James|title=7/24 WWE Battleground Results \u2013 CALDWELL\u2019S Complete Report|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/site/2016/07/24/jcbattlegroundppvreport/|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|date=July 24, 2016|accessdate=July 25, 2016}}</ref> At [[SummerSlam (2016)|SummerSlam]], Breezango competed in a 12-man tag team match, where their team lost. They then entered the [[WWE SmackDown Tag Team Championship]] [[WWE tournaments|tournament]], where they were eliminated in the first round by [[American Alpha]].\n\nOn the November 8 episode of ''SmackDown'', Breezango defeated [[The Vaudevillains]] to qualify for Team SmackDown for the [[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Elimination tag team matches|10\u2013on\u201310 Survivor Series Tag Team Elimination match]] at [[Survivor Series (2016)|Survivor Series]], where they were defeated by Team Raw, with them being the first team eliminated from the match. During this time, Breezango would undergo a slight gimmick change, where they began to refer themselves as \"fashion police\". On April 2, 2017, on the [[WrestleMania 33]] kickoff show, Breeze, along with Fandango, both entered the [[Andr\u00e9 the Giant Memorial Trophy|Andr\u00e9 the Giant Memorial Battle Royal]], but were unsuccessful.\n\nOn the April 25 episode of ''SmackDown'', Breezango defeated [[The Ascension (professional wrestling)|The Ascension]] in a beat the clock challenge match, becoming the number one contenders for the SmackDown Tag Team Championship at [[Backlash (2017)|Backlash]]. During the feud, Breezango turned face in the process. At Backlash, Breezango unsuccessfully challenged [[The Usos]] for the SmackDown Tag Team Championship. On the May 23 episode of ''SmackDown'', after Fandango and Breeze defeated Jimmy Uso and Jey Uso in singles matches, Breezango challenged The Usos for the titles that same night, but were once again unsuccessful. At [[Money in the Bank (2017)]], Breezango defeated The Ascension. Over the next few months, Breezango competed on Smackdown in various matches. On the [[Survivor Series (2017)]] Kickoff, they lost to [[Kevin Owens and Sami Zayn]]. At [[Clash of Champions (2017)]], Breezango lost to [[Luke Harper and Erick Rowan|The Bludgeon Brothers]]. They would go on to lose a rematch on the December 26 episode of ''SmackDown''. On the January 2 episode of ''SmackDown'', Breezango had another match with The Bludgeon Brothers and The Ascension tried to save them, but got beat down. On the January 9 episode of ''SmackDown'', Breezango defeated [[Rusev (wrestler)|Rusev]] and [[Aiden English]]. On the [[Fastlane (2018)|Fastlane]] kickoff show, Breezango and [[Tye Dillinger]] defeated [[Mojo Rawley]], [[Chad Gable]], and [[Shelton Benjamin]] in a six-man tag team match. On the April 3 episode of ''SmackDown'', Breezango, Tye Dillinger and [[Zack Ryder]] defeated [[Baron Corbin]], [[Dolph Ziggler]], [[Mojo Rawley]] and [[Primo Col\u00f3n]] in an eight-man tag team match. On the [[WrestleMania 34]] kickoff show, Breeze competed in the 30-man battle royal for the Andr\u00e9 the Giant Memorial Trophy, which was won by [[Matt Hardy]].\n\nOn April 16, during the [[2018 WWE Superstar Shake-up]], Breezango was drafted to [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]] brand. That same night, they defeated [[Cesaro and Sheamus]]. At the [[WWE Greatest Royal Rumble|Greatest Royal Rumble]] event, Breeze entered the match but was unsuccessful after being eliminated by Mojo Rawley. On July 6, it was reported that Fandango had suffered a left labrum tear in his shoulder that would put him out of action for six months, which was why Breeze had been inactive. On the December 12 episode of ''NXT'', Breeze appeared as the surprise opponent for [[Ricochet (wrestler)|Ricochet]]'s [[NXT North American Championship]] match in a losing effort. On the December 17 episode of ''Raw'', Breeze accepted [[Dean Ambrose]]'s open challenge for the [[WWE Intercontinental Championship|Intercontinental Championship]], which he lost. At [[WrestleMania 35]], Breeze competed in the Andr\u00e9 the Giant Memorial Battle Royal which was won by [[Braun Strowman]]. On April 14 at [[WWE Worlds Collide]], Breeze defeated [[Roderick Strong]].\n\n====Return to NXT (2019\u2013present)====\nOn April 25, 2019, Breeze started appearing at NXT live events.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cagematch.net/?id=2&nr=9500&page=4|title=Matches \u00ab Tyler Breeze \u00ab Wrestlers Database \u00ab CAGEMATCH - The Internet Wrestling Database|website=www.cagematch.net}}</ref> On the May 22 episode of ''NXT'', Breeze returned to NXT television where he interrupted [[NXT North American Championship|NXT North American Champion]] [[Velveteen Dream]] and took a selfie with him, but then attacked him. It was announced that Breeze would face Velveteen Dream for the NXT North American Championship at [[NXT TakeOver: XXV]]. Ultimately, Breeze lost the match. On the July 31 episode of ''NXT'', Fandango returned after a one year absence to rescue Breeze from the Forgotten Sons ([[Wesley Blake]], [[Jaxson Ryker]] and [[Steve Cutler]]) thus reuniting Breezango. Breezango would begin a feud with the Forgotten Sons defeating them in tag team action as well as in a six-man tag action with [[Isaiah \"Swerve\" Scott]] as their partner. However, in December, Fandango was once again sidelined with an injury leaving Breeze as a singles competitor. On the January 10 episode of ''205 Live'', he made his brand debut defeating [[Tony Nese]]. The following week, he defeated [[Ariya Daivari]].\n\n== Other media ==\nClement made a cameo appearance in an updated video for [[The Chainsmokers]] song \"[[Selfie (song)|Selfie]]\" in 2014, but not on the original music video.<ref>{{cite web|title=How Tyler Breeze became a part of the music video for the internet's biggest viral song|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/wwenxt/tyler-breeze-selfie-chainsmokers|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=June 2, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2016, Clement started his own [[YouTube]] series called ''Shootin' the Breeze'', where Clement portrays his Breeze character answering fan questions. The first five episodes were released on Clement's own YouTube channel, before being moved to WWE's channel in March.<ref>{{cite web|title=Shootin' the Breeze with Tyler Breeze|url=https://m.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLqIVmFaHA8BpIOEGhKRIfodUuEDSqXFE6}}</ref> \n\nBreeze is a recurring guest on Xavier Woods' YouTube channel UpUpDownDown, where he goes by the nickname 'Prince Pretty'. In November 2019, Breeze defeated [[Alexa Bliss]] in a game of ''[[Saturday Night Slam Masters]]'' to win the UpUpDownDown Championship, immediately after Bliss had won the championship in the finals of a ''[[Brawlhalla]]'' tournament.<ref name=\"SURVIVOR SERIES UPUPDOWNDOWN CHAMPIONSHIP LIVESTREAM\"> https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=GaAwxREMYuQ</ref>\n\nBreeze made his [[video game]] debut in ''[[WWE 2K16]]''. He has continued to appear as a playable character in ''[[WWE 2K17]]'', ''[[WWE 2K18]]'' and ''[[WWE 2K19]]'', ''[[WWE 2K20]]''.\n\n== Personal life ==\nClement married Ashley Miller, better known as [[Audrey Marie]], in September 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heartbreakers.me/index.php?/topic/9357-former-nxt-diva-audrey-marie-marries-tyler-breeze/|title=Former NXT Diva Audrey Marie marries Tyler Breeze|website=Heartbreakers - A Cult Fandom Forum}}</ref> In May 2019, Clement and [[Tye Dillinger|Ronnie Arneill]] (best known as Tye Dillinger) opened a wrestling school in [[Apopka, Florida]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=126481|title=TYLER BREEZE, TYE DILLINGER OPENING WRESTLING SCHOOL - PWInsider.com|website=www.pwinsider.com}}</ref>\n\n== Championships and accomplishments ==\n* '''[[Florida Championship Wrestling]]'''\n** [[FCW Florida Heavyweight Championship]] ([[FCW Florida Heavyweight Championship#Title history|1 time]])<ref name=FCWChampions />\n** [[FCW Florida Tag Team Championship]] ([[FCW Florida Tag Team Championship#Title history|1 time]]) \u2013 with [[Roman Reigns|Leakee]]<ref name=\"FCWChampions\"/>\n* '''[[Prairie Wrestling Alliance]]'''\n** PWA Tag Team Championship (1 time) \u2013 with Dan Myers<ref name=Cagematch />\n* '''''[[Pro Wrestling Illustrated]]'''''\n** Ranked No. 61 of the top 500 wrestlers in the [[Pro Wrestling Illustrated#PWI 500|PWI 500]] in 2015<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.profightdb.com/pwi-500/2015.html|title=Pro Wrestling Illustrated (PWI) 500 for 2015|accessdate=September 1, 2017|work=The Internet Wrestling Database}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category}}\n*{{wwe superstar|name = Tyler Breeze}}\n*{{facebook|TylerBreezePrincePretty}}\n*{{twitter}}\n*{{IMDb name|name = Mattias Clement}}\n* {{Professional wrestling profiles}}\n\n{{WWE personnel}}\n{{FCW Florida Heavyweight Championship}}\n{{FCW Florida Tag Team Championship}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Breeze, Tyler}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Canadian male professional wrestlers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Professional wrestlers from British Columbia]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Daytona Beach, Florida]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Penticton]]\n[[Category:American male professional wrestlers]]\n", "name_user": "183.87.129.2", "label": "