]]\n[[Category:2019 Indian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Indian television series]]\n[[Category:Colors (TV channel) series]]\n\n==External Links==\n\n* [https://www.voot.com/shows/shrimad-bhagwat-mahapuran/100812 Official website] on [[Voot]]\n* {{IMDB title|tt10426770}}\n", "text_old": "'''Shrimad bhagwat Puran''' is one of the 18 Mahapurans which were derived by breaking down the Veda's, as the intellect and life of human mortals was reducing with passage of time.The book '''Srimad Bhagwad Puran''' is a very sacred text comprising 12 chapters and one extra chapter written sometime later, about the breaking of Vedas into various Puran's and their significance. The Book explains the pointers by Naradmuni to Prithvi who is completely deprieved of its own virtues, the whole book  thereafter is a detailed question and answer between Shukdev ji and Maharaj Parikshit who is about to be killed by venom of serpent king Takshak, due to curse from son of Rishi.\n\nThe Shrimad Bhagwat Mahapuran covers concepts of universal formation , atom and its structures , outlining and description of earth, description of various major kings and dynasties from Bharat to kalki, references to various beahviours in Ramayan, Mahabharat, Krishna Rassleela in chapter 10 and thereafter a very detailed philosophy of life and virtues of this world.\n\nWhile the TV serial  potrays it in a complete different light, it should by no means be seen as a mere discussion between Radha and Krishna, in reality the discussion between Radha and Krishan ( Krish Raas section) is only a very limited part of it and can be seen as the last test, before the path to true knowledge is opened.{{Infobox television\n| show_name          = Shrimad Bhagwat Mahapuran\n| image              =\n| image_alt          = \n| show_name_2        =\n| genre              = [[Mythological]] <br> [[Drama]]\n| creator            = [[Nikhil Dwivedi]]\n| developer          = [[Nikhil Dwivedi]]\n| based_on           = {{plainlist|\n* [[Bhagavad Gita]]\n* [[Mahabharata]]\n* [[Ramayana]]\n}}\n| writer             = [[Vikas Kapoor]]\n| director           = [[Nikhil Dwivedi]]\n| creative_director = \n| starring         = [[Rajneesh Duggal]] <br> [[Shiny Doshi]]\n| narrated           =\n| opentheme          = ''Shirmad Bhagwat'' \u2013 song\n| endtheme           = ''Shrimad Bhagwat'' \u2013 music\n| composer           = \n| country            = [[India]]\n| language           = [[Hindi]]\n| num_seasons        = 1\n| num_episodes       = 47 <!-- as of 19 April 2020 --><!-- Do not uncomment the preceding text. This field is for a number only and the date should not be visible. -->\n| budget             = \n| list_episodes      = \n| executive_producer = \n| producer           = {{plainlist|\n* [[Nikhil Dwivedi]]\n}}\n| editor             = Paresh Shah\n| camera             = [[multi-camera]]\n| runtime            = 43 minutes \n| company            = Saffron Productions\n| distributor        = [[Viacom 18]]\n| network            = [[Colors TV]]\n| picture_format     = {{plainlist|\n* [[576i]]\n* [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n}}\n| audio_format       = \n| related            = \n| first_aired        = {{Start date|df=y|2019|6|2}}\n| last_aired         = present\n| website            = https://www.voot.com/shows/shrimad-bhagwat-mahapuran/100812\n| production_website = \n}}\n'''Shrimad Bhagwat Mahapuran,''' is an [[Television in India|Indian-Television]] [[Mythological]] series that airs on [[Colors TV]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/television/tv-channels/gecs/colors-shrimad-bhagwat-mahapuran-a-saga-blending-mythology-and-philosophy-190531|title=COLORS\u2019 Shrimad Bhagwat Mahapuran - A saga blending mythology and philosophy|last=|first=|date=2019-05-31|website=Indian Television|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref> every Sunday at 11:00 am. It premiered on 2nd June 2019. Its running time is around 45 minutes. The Shrimad Bhagwad cites and explains important aspects of  [[Bhagavad Gita]],[[Mahabharata]], [[Ramayana]] and [[Radha Krishna]] , but is my no means based on them , rather it is the Bhagwad which explains the principles and concepts behind these books in much greater detail.\n\n[[Shiny Doshi]] and [[Rajneesh Duggal]] are the main protagonists of the series along with an ensemble supporting cast including [[Ishita Ganguly]], [[Indraneil Sengupta]], [[Sonu Chandrapal]] and Priyanka Singh. The series is produced by [[Nikhil Dwivedi]] under the banner of Saffron Production.\n\n==Plot==\nIt is the Indian mythological story of 52 questions of [[Radha]] for [[Lord Krishna]]. These 52 questions based on or it will include Two Puran Gods event and two holy books event [[Ramayana]], [[Mahabharata]] and [[Bhagavad Gita]]. Radha questions Lord Krishna and he will answer to these questions. These questions are taken as per the questions that arise after watching or reading the mythological show or holy books. \n\n==Cast==\n* [[Shiny Doshi]] as Goddess [[Radha]]\n* [[Rajneesh Duggal]] as Lord [[Krishna]] \n* [[Ishita Ganguly]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tellychakkar.com/tv/tv-news/ishita-ganguly-and-indraneil-sengupta-colors-shrimad-bhagavad-180717|title=Ishita Ganguly and Indraneil Sengupta in Colors\u2019 Shrimad Bhagavad|date=2018-07-17|website= Tellychakkar Dot Com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-02}}</ref> as Goddess [[Parvati]]\n* [[Indraneil Sengupta]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tellychakkar.com/tv/tv-news/ishita-ganguly-and-indraneil-sengupta-colors-shrimad-bhagavad-180717|title=Ishita Ganguly and Indraneil Sengupta in Colors\u2019 Shrimad Bhagavad|date=2018-07-17|website= Tellychakkar Dot Com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-02}}</ref> as Lord [[Shiva]]\n* [[Vidisha Srivastava]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iwmbuzz.com/television/news/vidisha-srivastava-bags-colors-shrimad-bhagavad/2019/01/23|title=Vidisha Srivastava bags Colors\u2019 Shrimad Bhagavad|da